\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 The year of your marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh - 1930.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 The year of your birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 June 24th 1903.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh - in Treherbert at the head of the Rhondda Vale, Rhondda Valley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh I was born in a - in a little house - in - in Bute Street, Treherbert which wasn't quite big enough for us, and I think about a year.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Where did you live then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Then we removed then to a - a house which my father had built for us - in another part of the town. And - which was larger, much larger of course than the one that we - moved from.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you live in that house until the end of 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes, yes, from that time we lived there for - I think about twenty-five years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Your family moved because the first house was too small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes, the first house was too small and of course the family was growing and - my father had this house built for u
s specially, it was a larger house, a much larger.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh I have - two brothers and three sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Can you remember the birth order and the spacing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes, yes, now - my - my brother Garfield 
was the eldest and he - he was born in 1895, that's right, 1895. Then followed by Joyce in 1897. And - another girl, Irene, 1890. Then followed by my brother Trefor, 1900. And my sister Mildren 1901. Followed myself of course in 1903.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 So you were the baby of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes, that's right, I'm the baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 How old was your father when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Let me see now, my father, he would - he would be thirty-nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Do you remember where he came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. He came to Treherbert from 
the Merthyr area, Dalglas. When the pits were opening in the valleys here he came up here with his father to Treherbert.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What job did he do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well - I wouldn't be quite certain what job he did then but I do know this, that - he - moved from the T
reherbert area down to Swansea. Where he opened a - a coal - retail coal business in the Mumbles in Swansea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 And then he came back to Treherbert?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. Yes, he came back to Treherbert and then he - he was - he was on over}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 man in - one of the local collieries there. Yes. Colliery over}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 He had a coal retail business in Swansea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Coal retail business, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Before he became a colliery over}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did he have any jobs after?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No. No, no, he continued as a colliery over}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 man 'til he died. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did he do any casual or part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
No, I - no, I wouldn't think so. No, it was either in the mines or as I say that this business at - at the Mumbles and then back to the mines again. Which he continued until his dying - 'til he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Do you remember your father ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
No, I can't remember at all. In fact I can't remember much about my father because he died when I was about three years of age. No, very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 How old was your mother when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Let me see, oh, thirty-five my mother was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well my mother came from the - Somerset, from Somerset, from the - Mendip Hills area, a little village called Ubley actuall
y, at the foot of the Mendip Hills. Yes
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did she have any jobs before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh yes. When she came originally from - Somerset she - she went to Swansea and was employed there - in service with the - a family there, the Glasbrook family. They were local ship}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 owners in Swansea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 She was in service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 In service, yes, she was a parlour}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 maid I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did she work at all after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No. No, not any work at all whatsoever other than the home chores and - as mother and - wife, and wife and mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh no. No, no part time jobs those days not for people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 And she had a lot to do because she had all of you to bring up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes. Yes, well my father died you see when - when I was th
ree years of age and I don't know much about him. He died when he was forty-two. And - my mother had five children - to look after you see and bring up.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 So it was full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 It was a full time job, yes yes, oh indeed, those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Can I ask you about the household routine up until you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Yes, well my recollections of - my childhood were very happy. We didn't have much to spend but - I can really say that they were quite a - a happy time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You were in the house in Treherbert the longest weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes, well this house -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 How many rooms were at the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
It was the - six roomed house shall we say, three large bedrooms and three living rooms, the parlour, middle room as we used to call it those days, and the kitchen, and then there was a - a scullery bathroom and the usual offices downstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did anyone else besides your parents and brothers and sisters live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes - my cousin, my father's sister's son came to live with us when they
 came to Treherbert to live, or some time afterwards. His father had died you see, and - his mother presumably asked my father if he could find him a job which he did and he came to work in the colliery where my father was working. And he stayed with us u
ntil he married in later years. And of course my father's death also we had quite - a number of - lodgers with us at the house, in fact it was the only way my mother really managed to keep things going. She was of an independ}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 nt nature you know. She could h
ave gone to the Parish those days as we used to call it but - I don't think my mother ever did at all. We - she - she - worked really hard you know to bring us children up and - together with the money she had from the - the lodgers and of course my eldes
t brother who was eleven years of age at that time, went to work as well in the colliery as a dough boy in fact and - that's how we carried on actually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 And this cousin of yours stayed with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 He stayed with us until he married later on. Yes, sometime after the first world war. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did your mother pay anyone to help her in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
No. The help my mother had really was from my sisters you see, when they were growing up they did their little jobs and - helped my mother in all v
arious things which was required you see. Such as cleaning the boots you know the Sunday boots and put them away and - helping to - get the tea and some of the work which was required to do in the home.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes, all th
e washing was done at home, there was no laundries there. Never sent out, no. In fact I can only remember a few times when my mother was ill and she was unable to do it herself where you would employ a local washerwoman and - usually she did a day's work 
for about one and six you know those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 She would have somebody to come in if she wasn't well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh yes. To do things like that. Otherwise - otherwise the - work of the home was carried on by my sisters. On occasions like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 When you were in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Yes. Yes. Well - the only thing I can remember about school of course is - as I say we - we went to the local school there, the elementary school and - boys, junior first of all and - then into the boys school and - and eventuall
y, I - I tried the examination for the higher school and I - managed to get into the - Fourth County school which I went to eventually after - passing the examination.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did your mother or father mend or make the family clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. Well - after 
my father died of course my - as I told you my mother was - in that circumstances that - and of course she was able to do it, whether she would have done it had my father been alive I doubt very much but - the circumstances made her do things then and - p
ractically all our clothes, as children, was made by my mother. I think she made her own clothes as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Were the clothes new or second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well, a lot of them were shall we say second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 hand as far as the family was concerned. I would wear say 
my elder brother clothes as he grew out of them and I'd grow into his you see, and that sort of thing. Use was made of everything those days. Perhaps - the local tailors you see would sell - lengths of cloth which they had over which probably weren't suff
icient to make a - a man's clothes and they would come in handy for the boys clothes you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would your mother make suits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. Yes. Yes, I remember very well having a very fine Norfolk suit you know, you know, a Norfolk style suit and I can rem
ember that very well, in fact - I - there's a photograph which I've seen you know of our schooldays where the class was taken you know in the school surro}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 nd and I had this suit on that day, naturally we put our best clothes on you see to go to have that taken.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Your mother would make everything for all of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes, yes. Yes. Other than shall we say our - our socks, our woo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821 l}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 len socks and boots - and shoes and - we used to wear the old Eton collar as well you know which she used to wash you see at
 night, which came around your neck you know, it was a - a stiff - what you call it, not a plastic, it wasn't plastic. Celluloid, yes. And we had to wash those every evening of course to be ready for the next morning to go to school. That was the way - th
e things we used to do. At night we would go to perhaps - the Band of Hope. There wasn't much entertainment those days, other than you made yourself you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Where would she buy the clothes? Locally in Treherbert?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well - well, yes, I would think
 so, yes. She wouldn't go anywhere - oh perhaps relatives would send clothes to you. I think myself that her - her brothers were all farmers in Somerset, used to help us a lot. Yes, they would send clothes perhaps to her and she would - make them over you
 see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 So she wouldn't go to Cardiff to buy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh no. No thoughts - no, no thoughts at all of ever going to Cardiff - for things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What about shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well we had to buy all the shoes of course. And those were mostly - of course es
pecially the shoes that you use for the ordinary day school were - they were boots with hob nails in them you know, so they would last you for ever if possible. The only - lighter shoe you had were perhaps your best Sunday ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 When would you have new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well usually Easter time. It used to be always Easter time those times when you would have a new suit you see. Not only the people who were able to - who were - were - shall we say in bad circumstances, but even the rich people those days 
they always seemed to have a new rig out shall we say for Easter. I think so, yes. Yes And it - it seems to be that way now I fancy you know, that the winter goes over and the nice weather comes and you feel like having something new. Whether that's the r
eason for it I do not know but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You remember that's when you seemed to have them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes. Always - about Easter time, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What about shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh they were always bought, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Whenever you needed a new pair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Required them, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house, you were only three when he died weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes, I can't remember anything of that. I would think that - he would help her to a certain extent you know but - those da
ys of course it was - the home was left almost completely to the - the mother and the - the daughters you see. Presumably when we were quite young children no doubt he helped to a certain extent but - I have no recollection of that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you have any tasks you had to carry out regularly at home to help your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Yes. Well - the boys usually in a home, especially where there were girls, didn't do much of the work in the home. Other than shall we say - bringing the coal in for the following d
ay, maybe chopping the sticks. But me personally, I can always remember that on a Saturday morning I had to clean all the cutlery. The knives and forks and spoons etc, etc. And of course - those were cleaned those days on a kind of a sandstone you know or
 
a carbonundum - board you see. And - that was my job always on a Saturday and I - I always used to - always almost revolted over that you know because - I felt that on a Saturday morning I had to go out and play with the boys naturally. So - and especiall
y if my mother would come along and find that I hadn't done them very good to her - specifications you see, and of course then I naturally had to do them over again. So I learnt my lesson, I used to always - saw see that they were done well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 How long would you have gone on doing that, until you left school and went to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Yes. Yes, especially as I was the - the youngest you see. That was my job until I - when I was at school. Yes. Yes, until - no, until I went to school, until I went to the High
er Elementary school. I think my mother then sort of thought well I had plenty of work to do as far as homework and all that sort of thing by then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 So you didn't have any jobs then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 It was only when you were in the junior school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 In the junior school, yes. Until I was about - say, twelve or thirteen years of a And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 And then you went to the Higher Elementary School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 The Higher school, yes, Fourth Country school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You didn't have to do any jobs then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Other than fetching the coal perhaps and chopping sticks, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you do any jobs after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
No, well - when I left school you see it was during the war, the first world war, 1917 if I can recall. Things were getting pretty desperate 
at home those days. And - I - I had to leave school in order to help to keep the - the family going. And - I - I had a - a position as a junior clerk on the Tafvale Railway Company in Treherbert. I can recall that very well too because - I remember - my m
o
ther telling me that - that there was a job for me over at the Treherbert station and - this was during May 1917 and the weather was so nice you know, and I was an awful boy for going up the mountains and enjoying myself, I used to go fishing etc., so I h
a
d some nice time, and I thought this was about the Wednesday of the week, I can recall it very well. My mother said, you have to go over and see the Stationmaster the following day. So the next day I was dressed all up in all my best clothes and mother sa
w
 that my hair was parted properly and over I went to see the Stationmaster. So as I was going over I thought to myself, well now, I - I think I - I'll have this week off now, have a real good time and start work next Monday. Well when I got over to see th
e Stationmaster he asked me a few questions, he knew that I was in Porth County school and I'd passed well so he gave me a few - a few tests shall we say, writing and a few }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821 arithmetic}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821  - jobs, then he said, well - the job is yours, you see. And he said, when
 can you start? So I thought, oh well, I've thought this out well before. I said, next Monday, sir. What? He said, you'll go and start immediately. And in I had to go and start in the booking office straight away in Treherbert. Much to my regret of course
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 So you didn't have to do any jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Not then, no, not after that. Not in the house. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did your brothers and sisters have regular jobs to do in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well I think the girls always helped the mother you see, in a
ll the various work. My elder brother, when my father died, he was eleven years of age, and he went to work in the colliery where my father was the over}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 man, and he worked as a dough boy. And of course he helped you know to keep the family going.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 So he wouldn't have done any jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 He wouldn't have had a job in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Not in the house, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What about your other brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 My other brother, when he was quite young after he finished school - he was taken to - by my uncle
 to Somerset and they intended teaching him the farming industry, and so I don't remember much about him until he returned - from Somerset. No. I think that he probably would have done the jobs that I had to do when he was - when I was quite a little boy 
perhaps you know and he did the - the - cutlery, and then it fell to my lot, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 And your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 They would help my mother in all the various chores in the house you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You don't remember if they were given definite jobs or did they do everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well I wouldn't say definite - any definite job, it's just a sort of - general help to my mother, all the various things they could do. 'Cos they did eventually go out to work in various shops in Treherbert.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did the older children help the younger children with things they found difficult?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Dressing you or eating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Yes, I would think that - the elder sister or brother would help the younger one - you know, to do various things, help - wash - you know, help 
to dress him in the bedroom perhaps you know and that - those sort of things you see. Until you were able to do it yourself you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You don't remember them looking after you in any particular way or any other way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes, I - I always remember my 
brother you know, I can remember this very well, especially on a Sunday we would attend the local church you see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 This is your oldest brother?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 The next - no, the next one from me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 That's Trefor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes, we were more - shall we say toge
ther than my elder brother, because we were quite - near each other in age you see, but he - we would come home from - from church, perhaps chapel on a Sunday night, mother perhaps would stay to the second meeting and that sort of thing you see, and we wo
u
ld come home and the first thing he would do when we got in you know was go to the pantry and we'd have a tuck in you know of the old jam and apple tarts and whatever there was going you know especially on a Sunday, but - I can recall very well perhaps ou
r
 clothes be torn you know, especially in the seats you know and we would do the - the mending ourselves. My brother would teach me the way to do it. And I can often remember doing great - putting great patches on the seats of our trousers, and feeling ver
y very - bucked about it, we were able to do it. But we did things like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 So the younger children would help the older children in that way, you'd do little jobs around the house together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Together, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 But you particularly remember about the mending?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh indeed I do. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. My mother - that's one thing my mother did was keep us to strict hours of going to bed. It was - it was on very ra
re occasions that we went over certain hours, and those hours I think until I got to the age of ten and eleven years of age must have been about eight o'clock, half past eight. Nine o'clock would be the latest. The really latest. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did your mother put you to bed or anyone else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well when we were quite young of course she would put us to bed. And - probably have a bath you know, something like that, if we was very dirty or something like that we would be bathed and put to bed but - and - and mo
ther would take us to bed and - or tell us to go on up the stairs to bed and she would come upstairs and tuck us in after saying the prayer and - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You remember only your mother taking you up or would somebody else do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 I remember my -
 my brothers younger - younger - when I was quite younger perhaps my brothers would sometimes take us up, but on rare occasions. It was usually - always mother, yes. Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What age did you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh I - I think that we - we go
t you know eventually to - we were taught you know to do things for ourselves very much by our mother. I suppose the circumstances made it that way because she was so busy with various things. But she taught us to be - to do things for ourselves you see a
nd we got to do things - I should think that about - seven, eight, nine years of age we put ourselves to bed, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you share the bedroom or the bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes. Yes, we were so many in family you know 'course eventually my mother kept lodgers in 
the home and of course my cousin came with us as well from Swansea. And we would perhaps sleep - in one room, the boys would sleep together or young men as we'd call them, I was quite a youngster, we would be sleeping perhaps four in a bedroom. Two large 
beds you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You and your brother in one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Yes. The only furniture - there would perhaps be a big - perhaps chest of drawers you know where you had one drawer and - each one had a drawer you see for your clothes. You don't have much clothes
, just you - your - your everyday clothes and your Sunday clothes you see, your best you used to call it but - and then of course my - sisters would sleep with my mother in another bedroom and the lodgers would sleep in - this other bedroom. We had three 
large bedrooms there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Do you remember if there were two beds in each bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Usually, yes, two beds in each bedroom. Yes. And there was no small beds those days of the - say singles see, they were always large - double beds you know, four foot six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 So you were always two in a bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh - usually, yes. Until - later on you know in life when some of us got - me elder brother got married or something like that you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Up to the end of the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You were about fifteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You were sharing a bed with your brother 'til then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh - yes. Yes, sharing a bed with my brother. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well we - our bath was in the - the scullery, there was a scullery bathroom you see downstairs. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 A lean-to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
No. No, it was quite a large - it was quite a large - scullery bathroom, and lead in off from there of course would be the pantry you see, And then of course another part of that would be the toilet. Outs
ide which you approached from the outer yard you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 How often did you bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well - depends entirely on - how dirty you were when you came home from playing you know with the boys sort of thing. If you were really dirty mother would make you go
 into the bath you see and - and have a bath because - there wasn't any question of being short of water those days you see, you had the coal free from the colliery and there was plenty of water there always. So - but - usually it was once a week shall we
 say on a Saturday. Saturday night was always bath}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
night. And you changed your clothes you see on Saturday night. Ready for Sunday, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 But if you were very dirty from playing you'd have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You'd have a bath, yes. Or, shall we say 
a wash down. A jug in the bath you see, it was easier to go in there than to be just washed you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh that was once a week again, usually after the Saturday night bath you see. All fresh for Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you have a part time job or any means of earning a little regular money while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Yes. Yes. I can remember - I can remember when I was quite a young boy, I - I don't think I was much more than about ten or eleven years o
f age - one of the elder boys of the vicinity asked me if I would like to go to work in a - in a - a hairdressers, a barbers shop what they called in those days, still call them I suppose. And of course I - I - I - I said, yes, I would like the job. Well 
o
f course I have to go there now in the evenings, this was in the local hairdressers and barbers shop and I was working as a lather boy as we called them. You would shave - you would lather the - the - men used to come there you know and - the man then of 
c
ourse would do the shaving you see. And you'd sort of clear them off help to put their coat on, etc., etc., you know, and sometimes when you did that the was a little tip at the end of it, sometimes a penny or a ha'penny which was - quite a lot of money t
hose days you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did the barber pay you regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Yes, no, I had the - I had the enormous wage of two shillings a week. And that included working every evening in the barber's shop and - except the Thursday of course when they had a half day
, and on Saturday all day on a Saturday. But that included my meals, my dinner and my tea, which you had in - on the premises.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What about Sunday, you didn't work on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh not on a Sunday, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 And half day was Thursday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Half day was Thursday, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you have any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh no, no, no. There were no holidays actually with those jobs you see. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 How did you get the job, you just heard about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes - I saw this boy you know who was working in t
his barber's shop especially and they wanted another boy and so he asked me and - I said I would take it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 That's all you did actually, you just had to lather the men?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Lather the men, yes. And I can recollect very well you know some of th
e local - men you know in Treherbert there, we thought were well-to-do - some of the grocers there you know, and they had their own shaving mugs you know and their own brush as well and soap. And they were kept in a kind of a little - locker affair you kn
o
w on the side in the shop there and - you knew them eventually when they came in, you knew that he was being shaved next and you'd bring this down you know because - they used to be afraid so much those days of - what they called a kind of a barber's rash
,
 you see, so'd they'd keep their own - mugs you see. 'Course the poorer ones went - they had the usual ones which were - were count for everybody. Well of course - the big men you know, those ones we used to look after specially you see. Bigger tip off th
em, in fact it was only from them you would have a tip really. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What would you get for a whole week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well two shillings a week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 That included the tips?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you feel that was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, that was exclusive of the tips. Yes, yes, the tips were some -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You wouldn't remember how much you'd have altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh - not much. It would be perhaps - you would be very fortunate - perhaps on a Christmastime you know there was usually a box put there for the rather boy you see. And then perhaps everybody would put a three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 penny bit in or something like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you feel it was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well - it didn't strike me at all whether it was fair or otherwise. It - you know - it was a sort of - so
mething to do and something to probably, which I thought, to help the home going because - I didn't keep the money myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You started doing that when you were about eleven, did you go on doing it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, I wasn't there very long. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 That was the only job you had while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 I gave it all to my mother. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You don't know what it was spent on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh no. It helped to - you know - to keep the home going shall we say, whatever - whatever way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 How did you get on with the other people who worked with you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 In the barber's shop? Well - the - the - the - the business was a - a - two brothers, and they had two shops, and - the younger brother 
was rather - I thought rather officious in his way you know. He - he didn't have much compunctions shall we say for the - young boys who were working there. He want to work and work really hard, that's what I used to feel with him. But when I used to go u
p
 to the top shop as we used to call it, which was another part of the town, he was an elder brother and he was very nice. He - you know - you felt that - you - and you felt really in the end that you could do more for him than you could for the younger on
e. The younger one treated you rather off handed you know shall I say.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What hours did you actually have to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well - after coming from school and getting home and having tea you'd go down to the shop you see, which would be shall we say - fiv
e o'clock you see, and you would work ten - of course, I don't know really whether the office hours, you know, shops and office hours was in operation then, I think they were just about probably coming in well they couldn't employ young - children you kno
w after certain hours. I don't know for certain, but I do - I think I used to finish about the - in the week nights probably by about seven or eight o'clock you see, to - say two hours. But on a Saturday it was all day until about nine o'clock at night.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What time in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Nine o'clock. Nine 'til nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 When your mother wasn't very busy in the house how did she spend her time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well she - she went visiting to - shall we say friends of hers, near you know to our home, and - spent sha
ll we say an hour or so with the mother or the - the family there you see and had a - chat really over about things, otherwise there was - nothing at all otherwise that my mother did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 She didn't have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, she had n
ot time really to - do much otherwise than - just - it was when you see that - we boys and girls all started to work and things came a little bit easier shall we say financially in the home that - my mother could find any time shall we say to - devote sha
ll we say to any relaxation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
No, there was - there was nothing really - there was nothing really in - there was very rare that - that there was anything, you know, in the the town other than - than no - shall we say eistefo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 ds or - there was the - there was the local - there was an opera house in Treherbert, of course they had variety shows there, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would your mother ever go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 I don't think my mother ever went there. No. She wasn't - well I don't
 think she - she would spend the money you see too go to places like that. The money wasn't available shall we say to - to utilize you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 She wouldn't take part in any sport of any description?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Not at all. No, not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 She wouldn't go to a club or a pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh no, no,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821  cer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 tainly not, no. No. Dead against it in fact.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did she belong to any savings clubs, boot club, sick club or funeral club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, I can't remember - no, I can't remember anything like that, and I - I would actu
ally think that my mother didn't belong to anything like that because it was a question then of what ever money came into the home went out as well, the same - you know, in the same week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well -
 very well. We - we enjoyed ourselves. As children, you know, and we - we were quite attached to one another, in fact we've been attached to each other ever - all through our lives and - it - I think it showed that that we had a happy u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821 p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 bringing you know together to be - that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Was there one you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes, yes, I think the brother next to me I felt - more attached to him than any of the others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 That wasn't Garfield?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 That - that's - that was Trefor. Yes, he was 
next to me you see. I used to think that he was my ideal shall we say you see and I used to look up to him so much you know. And he used to care for me for a lot too as well. Yes. He - he would look after me you know and when we used to go out to shall we
 
say - out to run when he was a boy, you know - in school as well and I was in school you see, we would go up the mountains and he would - take care of me you see and then I - naturally took a - you - you went nearer to him than shall we say your other bro
ther. And we slept together. Oh yes, we did. Oh indeed. That's right, yes, yes. That's right. Perhaps that was the reason.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 When you were a child who did you play with, would it be just your brothers and sisters or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 We played with neigh
bours as well you know, there were neighbours - families you know, quite as large as us. And there was boys perhaps and girls there of the same age and who - you naturally played with them you see, you went to school with them and then you played with the
m as well.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Where would you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh - either - not much in the homes. But - other than shall we say playing games, but - the games otherwise would be more outdoor you know. In the street, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Not in the yard or the houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh no. Str
eet play, yes. In fact against the - the end wall of the house you know yes, we played ball games against there you see. That's if the people in there would allow it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did they come out and shout at you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. Sometimes. We used to play games like
 weak horses and things like that. We'd pick a team you see. Weak horses we'd call it. k And one team would go against the wall - like a scrummage. Men in the scrummage, one against the other you know that, and the others now would - would take a - a flyi
n
g jump and jump onto your backs you see. And then the next one would come onto them again,. And the next one, until the whole of the other team was there now. And if you held them, well - they had to go down. But if you fell down well you were weak horses
 you see and you'd have to stand again for the next jump. You see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You didn't have bats or anything to play with did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No. No. If we made - if we had played with any sort of cricket we would make our own - our own bat you see, make it out of w
ood of some description and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What about a ball?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well - I don't know what balls we played with. Sometimes perhaps we'd have a cricket ball from somewhere or other, but it wasn't the cricket ball, the leather ball, it was a composition ball. You 
see, which were much cheaper. And we played with those. And we used to play - marbles you know and things like that you know. Make a ring and put some - so many marbles in and - it was really - marvellous that some of these boys you know could play, as I 
s
ay they would - they would piddle the ring as we call it you - see, you put so many in and one would shoot and once his tor as we called it, the one he shot with with his - with his thumb, went outside the ring somebody else would have a try. But some of 
t
hese boys were so well - in - in this game of marbles that they would hit one out, hit another one out and they would - they would - they would knock their tors we'd call it in such a way that it would spin you know and it would come back. It wouldn't go 
forward, it would come back after it had hit the - it was like - like men playing snooker you know on a snooker table. The side that they could put on them, it was wonderful the way that some of these boys could do it. I could never do it myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 There were no parks to play in?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, no. No, only on the mountains, on open ground you know around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Were those the winter games or the summer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well marbles is in the summer you know and - and we used to play a - a game called catty and dog as w
e used to call it. You would shape a piece of wood, you know, on the end - like into a point, and on the other end into a point, and you would have it dog as we'd call it which would be - something like the size or the shape of a - of a - a constable's tr
u
ncheon - truncheon you see. And you would - you would hit the - the end of this catty, which was the catty, and knock it on the floor and you'd tamp up into the air, and then you'd hit it you see as far as you could. You see? Well that would start from th
e door as we called it you see. It was almost like playing baseball, American baseball, rounders, yes. Only homemade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you run round then, in a circle, was it a team or individual?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Sometimes - a team, yes. Sometimes you would make it into this
 run around business, but usually we would play in the lanes you know between the houses, and then you couldn't go sideways - it had to be straight you see. And then - the other - the opposing team would be there and as you hit this catty as we call it in
to the air, if they caught that catty you see you were all out. And then they would win like that you see. And all that sort of thing. It - it was very interesting. Used to play teams you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What about scotch, did they play scotch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well, the - 
the girls would play scotch, we thought it was a - a - you know, a girlish game to play scotch. We would play skipping. Do a lot - do a lot of skipping, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Tie one end to the lamp post?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No. No, it wasn't that - it wasn't that - that ty
pe. Individual skipping. Yes. And we could - and we could do anklets, you know, quick skipping you know. Fast, very fast. Yes, could count, yes, we did, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Anything else you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well - I think those were the main ones really for 
outdoor, we played a ball game against the wall you know. One hitting the ball - well it was - yes, it was something like - squash ra}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821 cke}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 ts you know. Squash shall we say see. Only there'd be no ra}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821 ck}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
et, you'd use a hand. And you'd hit that against the wall y
ou see and then the opposing team would have to have - the hit, and he would hit it against the wall and then the other one would have to - go the other side and hit it against the wall. One after the other, you know, that sort of thing you know. It - it 
was - it - it made you fast you know and quick you see and all that sort of thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 This was on the end of a house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Point end of a house, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 There wasn't much traffic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh no, no traffic, no. And by the time we'd be playing in the aft
ernoon maybe even the milk floats would have been all in you see. And ash carts would have been all in. Very peaceful, peace, yes, you had the place to yourself sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh well - it wasn't a 
question of allowing, you to get dirty, we just got dirty. You know. The roads were not made you see. Except the main road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 But your mother wasn't cross if you did get dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, I - no, I think my mother - realized the fact you know that that w
as the only fun that we could have and then - she allowed us, and if we came home dirty, as we did, especially in the holiday times, in fact in holiday times your - your mother would give you any old clothes to wear because they'd be such a state you see,
 
but - as far as being allowed to get dirty well - that didn't sort of enter - enter into it. You just played a game and if you got dirty you got home and fortunately we had a bath and plenty of got water, and was into the bath, have a wash, and off to bed
 you see. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Were you free to play with anyone that you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Yes. My mother never - no. Sometimes my - I think my mother was a bit concerned sometimes about things. Especially - during those days you know tuberculosis was rive you see, espe
cially in the valleys, and - 'cos it's even known today that it - it was - contagious you see and - mind those were days when they didn't know really what was the cause of it as well, it was - sometimes they used to say it was because they weren't having 
e
nough food and all that sort of thing, but - even so - that was the only time when I used to think my mother would be a bit concerned perhaps if you were playing with somebody who they knew perhaps - had this you see. And - and it was about you know a lot
 you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 That was the only reason?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 That's the only reason, mother never stopped us otherwise, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you belong to any youth organisation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No. No, no, there - there was no youth organisati}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821 
ons in our - in our town what}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 soever - not of any description. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What about your free time when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 When you were very little did you have any hobbies, what did you do when you came home from school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No. Well - as I say either went - if it was Band
 of Hope you went with the Band of Hope you see, and - and then - otherwise, the nights, especially in the winter, if it in dark you seen we were put to bed by seven and eight o'clock. Earlier than that probably if we were - younger you see. And then - in
 
the winter nights perhaps you' have a game of draughts with your brother and - and especially the next brother which I - who I mentioned to you, Trefor, we would have a lot of games together and he used to pull my leg unmercifully. Oh I used to get in suc
h
 a tear with him and he would laugh you know. Oh dear, you know, playing draughts you see, he would pretend to move - and he wouldn't do it and I'd be waiting for him to do it you see so I could take about three or four off him and then he - he - he'd go 
against it se and put it back you see. Very funny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You mentioned that you had a rabbit once?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Yes, I - I had a rabbit. I had a few in fact but - you know, we didn't know the way really to look after them those days. You see - rabbits require - cer
tain food and - we used to give 'em bran that I can remember but they wanted so much greens an things like that you see to keep themselves fit and live and they would eventually die you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you have anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, only a rabbit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No dog?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No. And sometimes of course - sometimes a cat would - would - kill the rabbit you see. 'Cos there was plenty of cats around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 But you didn't have one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes, we had a cat, yes. Oh yes, had a cat, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you always keep a cat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Mostly, yes. Yes, I think it was about the only thing that we did ever keep was a cat, we never had a dog.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Nor a bird or anything like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, no birds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You didn't collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No. No, I don't think so, I don't think - we u
sed to collect shells and things like that when we used to go to the seaside. Pebbles and things like that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Girls used to collect wild flowers and press them didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. Yes. Oh yes, that's right, we would go nesting you know. And - a
nd get birds eggs, yes. We would make a hole in the end you know and blow them and - and then - you'd have a - a set of these kind of - eggs you see. But if we came to a nes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821  where the - the - youngsters were born you know it would be very interesting, we 
would be going there practically - once every day just to see how they were getting on. And then all of a sudden they would be gone you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would you take all the eggs in a nest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh no. Only take one. Yes. Take one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you do any gardening, did you have much of a garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
We had a little garden at the back of our house, not very large but it was - it wasn't a - you know - it was mostly ash you see, it wasn't very thick for doing much - shall we say gardening and it was mostly flowers 
we had there. Which my mother - tended to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you do anything in the garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
The only gardening I did was during the war. When we had this allotment. And then it was mostly helping my brother, I couldn't do much, I was a - quite a youngster you
 know, wasn't strong enough to do it really. But I used to do something you know to help him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 That was Trefor was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, my eldest brother, Garfield.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you ever go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. In the mountain streams there were trout in the strea
ms you know, and I think there were trout eventually in the river but - mostly I think because of the - of the filth that used to come from the collieries then, it would kill them you see. But there were trout up in the books in the mountains and we used 
t
o go up - there you know certain times of the year and - start tickling trout as we'd call it you see. Pushing our hands underneath the bank and stones and - you would feel a treat there and tickle that see. And then you pull them out and oh my gracious l
i
fe, if you had one of those used to take it home then to have a meal you know. Oh dear me, you seemed to think you had one of the biggest fish you're ever going to get. Oh yes. Yes. Otherwise - otherwise there was no fishing really as you might say fishin
g with a rod or anything like that then, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You went for walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh of course, yes, a lot of walks. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No bicycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 I did have a bicycle given eventually - but that was going on when I started work. And then I - did quite a lot 
of cycling around the place. You know, you didn't go very far, it was mostly in the town and we went perhaps - as far as Treorchy, about as far as you could go. Or you dare - or you dared go because you - you - you sort of - thought you was going a bit to
o - a bit too far out of your way you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you take part in any sports at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh well - the sports really that were - in operation those days that I knew of was only the school sports and the - the - church, the chapel sports you know. And 
usually I - I came out very well in those, I - I got books today you know which was given to me like testaments - new testaments and - and various books such as Tom Brown's Schooldays and all that which was give to you now for prizes in the school sports.
 
And - skipping and running and - and of course eventually of course - I - I progressed in - into young manhood and manhood and - and still kept on with it you know and I - I won quite a number of good prizes eventually, as a professional mind see. Running
 as a professional for money those days, there wasn't much amateur about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Was that before the end of the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh no, after the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you go to many theatres at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes, sometimes. There was a theatre in Treherbert, the opera house.
 And - but it was very rare occasions, if we went there it would be probably - to a matinee - on a Saturday afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes, sometimes concerts in the - church, but not otherwise. Not - at that age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No music halls?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 While you were still at school you would just go to the matinee?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Yes, until the local cinema, which had only just opened then you know, just about - prior to the - '14 -'18 war. That's the only enjoyment we had shall we say other than
 making our own - fun you know and etc., was to go to the matinee on a Saturday afternoon and we paid about a penny I think to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Very little. Until I started work. No pocket money whatsoever - we had no -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well usually in our - in our kitchen you see, which was the - almost the living room you know for the - all the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Were there any occasions when you ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Sometimes. Perha
ps - maybe on special occasions such as - shall we say a birthday party or maybe perhaps a - Christmastime we may go into the other room you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Was that the parlour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes, the middle room usually. Not the parlour, the parlour would be really t
he special room you know in the front of the house. But this'd be the middle room as we call it, the next to the kitchen you see. But separate from the actual kitchen, a passage going away to the front of the house you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Where you had you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821 r meals was sort of the kit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 chen really where your mother cooked the meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh yes. Yes yes, the living room where everything was done practically, other than shall we say the washing up and the bathroom and all that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Where was the cooking equipment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh the cooking equipment was in the kitchenette as we called it, or the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Not where you ate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would it be a range or a gas stove?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 A gas stove we had in our place, yes, we had a gas stove there. But
 we - but we - we also had of course in - in the kitchen itself the range you see, where you do she we say the - the - the cooking of the meat and things like that, but - usually if it was the midweek meals they were done usually in the - scullery as we c
all it where the gas stove was you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 It was a black}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 lead sort of range was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Yes. With the - shall we say this - steel bars you know in front of it which was - little bit of a decoration those days you know, about the only thing - otherwise it was all black and was black}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 leaded.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 So your mother had the two, the cooking range and the gas stove?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Two means of - of cooking, yes. Coal, that's right, and the gas cooker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Where was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh in the same room, the - in the middle - our main room which we - we would call shall we say our living room then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What members of the family would be present for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well we'd be up at all times, my brother of course, he'd go to work early in the morning to the loca
l pit you see and he'd leave home probably about - six o'clock to walk to the - to the colliery. And he'd probably have his breakfast probably about half past five I would think - some of that region. Well the rest of us then going on you see when I was e
m
ployed in - eventually once I - once I started on the railway, I - when I was on the day shift as we called it, I used to start at six o'clock in the morning and of course it was - it was quite an early - breakfast then for shall we say my elder brother a
nd myself. And - we - we used to come home as well to the midday meal you see, which was twelve o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 So for breakfast you and your brother would be together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Wed have it about the same time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What about the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well the rest of 
my brothers - my - it depends really on where they were or what work they were doing you see. If they were - if they were on a - I was on that - at that time on a - on a - two shift you see, a day shift and an afternoon shift in the booking office. And of
 course it - depended then entirely if you - if you were on the afternoon shift you were probably in bed 'til about nine or - ten o'clock in the morning, your mother allowed you there you see, so we had -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 So really the breakfast was in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821 instalments}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh indeed, yes, yes, all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 How about when you were in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
When you were in school it was practically always the same time. If we were all going to school which we were most of us you see if I was quite - I was quite the youngest 
but - my eldest brother other than - you know, before he started work we were all going to school and we would all have our breakfast about practically the same time then, see, which would be about eight o'clock I would think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What would you have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well - we - we used - we used to mostly - those days if we had - bread and butter and jam and - usually in the winter we would always have porridge, my mother always gave us porridge first thing. And - and then we'd have - bread and butter
, perhaps toast but it was unusual to have shall we say an egg or bacon and egg and things - such things as that. It was a - considered practically a luxury as far as our home was concerned. Those days you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What did you have to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh, it was cocoa sometimes. We'd have cocoa or tea. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you have anything different on Sundays or Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Sometimes, on a Sunday I think it was usually the special day of the week, where we may have say on a - a breakfast time we would have pe
rhaps some bacon or an egg fried and - we used to have also lava bread those days. We had - used to have it sent up from the Mumbles and - on a Sunday morning would have the lava bread which was a kind of a cake you know, it was - shall we say picked off 
the rocks you know on the sea shore and made into a - it was boiled and cleaned and all that sort of thing and - we were held - it would be fried in the bacon fat with - Sunday morning breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 When you say it was sent up how did you get it, did you buy it off the cockles women at the door?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Sometimes off the cockle}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 women on the door, used to come from the - the Swansea area you know, Pencloud that way, they would come - usually on a Saturday too and they would come around the doors you see. And 
sell - ooh, quite large quantities of it in the Rhondda Valley those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would you have it regularly every week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Not every week, no. No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Do you remember what you had for midday meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well - we would have a cooked meal usually 
on a midday meal. Usually a cooked meal of some description. Might be - well - usually on the - say the Monday or the Tuesday it would be the leave over of the cold - of the meat from the Sunday joint you see. And - perhaps you'd have - potatoes fried wit
h
 it. But it was usually a cold meal on a Monday, you could always bank on that, it was a - a cold meal. On the Tuesday perhaps - you' have - perhaps - some meat of some description. I don't know really, take me back quite a time to think of these other th
ings that you had those days, because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What would you have in the evening, another cooked meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Now - no, never a cooked a meal in the evening, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You had a breakfast and then your main dinner midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Breakfast, main dinner midday, y
es. Then for tea you'd have the usual bread and butter and jam or you might have a banana with it or - something like that, you might perhaps - your mother might have made some - might have made a pudding perhaps, a rice pudding and you'd have that with b
read and butter you see and enjoy it really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What about Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh Sunday for tea it was always a special tea, blancmange and jellies and things like that you know. Tarts as well you see. Apple tarts, whatever the fruit was going in season then y
ou see. There was plenty of that sort of thing. And - usually - those tarts - went over from the Sunday as well, to a few days shall we say of the week you see, which provided quite a - a background or shall we say - your - your second course or whatever 
you like to call it today, or your sweet then, which would be called today you see, and - you'd have a piece of tart and some custard perhaps on it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Sunday dinner would be different from the rest of the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes. That was always the m
ain joint you see, you'd have a joint perhaps of beef or a shoulder of lamb or - leg of lamb or whatever the case may be. Usually -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 When you were in school, when you were as young as that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes, oh yes, yes. The - it was always a sort of a - Sund
ay was the main meal of the week you can say, with all the family - usually were gathered together as well which made it that way. And - and then - in the week it was perhaps chops and things like that you see would make the meal or - perhaps you'd have a
 - what shall we call - the Welsh would call cowl, but - broth you see, and you'd have a piece of a - neck or something like that you see of the meat and then all kinds of vegetables is it and dough boys.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did your mother bake her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh y
es, mother baked - all the bread that we used to use. Was very rare that we bought anything from a baker. We used to take in fact the - the bread to the bake hou}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821 
se you know, there was local ba}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 ke}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
houses there - almost - almost every - part of town where we live and - most of the people - when I was quite a young child - they they baked their own bread. And we used to go there in the evening and bring it back you see from the bake}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 house and - take it home. Big large loaves, they were as - almost as big as ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would your mother do it every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh no. No, it would be about - say about perhaps - twice or three times a week. Oh I think twice - be quite sufficient because they were very large loaves and be perhaps - two or three you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Then the children would have to take them to the baker's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Yes, you see we took them and brought them back for her. In the afternoon you see, if we take them perhaps - we used to take them I think when we used to go back to school, it was on our way to s
chool you see, and then - in the evening then after we come back from school and after perhaps tea - we would go and get the bread you see. And of course on the way back home we'd be pulling off the crusts off the side of the tin and - helping ourselves t
o the - most enjoyable new bread you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did she make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
No, my mother - I don't think my mother made anything of that kind. She was too much involved really in - in keeping the home going you know and looking after the - the lodgers or - who we had quite a few at - in our house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What about bottling fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
No, not anything of that kind at all. We - we were living in the Rhondda Valley you know, there was not much fruit grown locally at all. And - whatever fruit
 you bought then was very cheap in the shops. Fruit was - was one of the cheapest commodities I think you could buy because - you know, the trainloads and truckloads of - apples and things like - that would be brought in from - the - fruit growing distric
ts, Somerset and - Worcester and Gloucester and - you know. It - it was very cheap and we bought whatever fruit we required.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 And vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Vegetables as well, yes. It was only after the 1914-'18 war really that the allotments came into operatio
n you see where we had an allotment then and of course we grow a - a bit of vegetables, mostly potatoes you see, to keep things going.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 She wouldn't bottle any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh no. No, there was no bottling done in Treherbert, nor preserving whatsoever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did she make pickles at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Wine or medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No. Never anything at all - like that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 There wasn't any beer brewed for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No. No, nothing of that kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You grew your own vegetables during the war but not before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh no, not before that. There was very little vegetables grown really in the - in the mining districts then you know, the men were working in the collieries, but - the war brought it - did bring it on to a certain extent and I think that 
after the war that - most of the people kept their allotments going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Your mother bought fruit for you and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What about tinned or dried vegetables or tinned fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well - yes, we used to have tinned fruit I remember
 always it was a delicacy really you know on a weekend or something like that where we used to have perhaps a - a tin of - pineapple chunks you see. That was the main - you know, those days. There wasn't - there were pears as well, but I think pears were 
- shall we say a - a higher priced tinned fruit than the pineapples which were quite a cheap - buy, what I can remember those days, and that's what we had mostly was - if there was any in that line it would be perhaps pineapple chunks you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You didn't keep any livestock, hens or pigs or goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
No, we - no, we didn't. We - lots of people did but we never did. We - only as I - perhaps had a rabbit when as a pet - as a pet you see but not to keep anything otherwise, not of the - anything in the - poultry line.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would you have meat at the weekend and during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh I would think - naturally there'd be the - the joint on a Sunday which would be a large joint and that would go over then probably - for two meals other than Sunday joint 
you see, it would be probably - eaten cold on a Monday and then perhaps it would be minced you see or made into a pie or something like that for another day. Maybe for the Wednesday. We'd probably have fresh meat then on the Tuesday, 03 - I don't think we
 
used to have fish. Fish really those days was on a weekend, what I can remember. And now you know it's mostly a Tuesday meal, fish, or at least it is with us, but those days I think - fish really - was very cheap again what I can remember. They used to co
me around you know, the fishmongers with his open - carts and sell you fish, you could get herrings I would think about a dozen for - about sixpence those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You'd have fish once a week would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 We'd have them probably then, yes. But I don't
 think it was a regular meal shall I say like it is today. You have a fish meal today, we had a fish meal now every week on one day but - not so much-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15480826\charrsid3146821 You did}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 n't have regularly fish one day, meat the next?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 But you'd have meat about four days of the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Four days a week I should think, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would you have had any tinned meat, there was corned beef about then wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well I - I think corned beef came into - into - into the shops and to be known as well
 during the - during the - the first world war. I think that corned beef was imported into the country but we didn't have much of that, what I can remember. But during the war of course we did because I mean it was - almost -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you ever have extra meat such as rabbit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 From poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh we'd have rabbit. Not from poaching, because there was no rabbits around, not poached rabbits, no. No, no rabbits whatsoever. Think there were a few mountain hares but - I never saw one myself ever. But -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You'd buy rabbit from the butcher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Yes, and we used to have them sent to us by our uncles - from Somerset. And - use. They - they had farms there you know and we would have a - perhaps sent to us you see and - we might sometimes have a pheasant sent to us too. But that was on theirs.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 How often do you think you might have rabbit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh - well we'd have - we'd have rabbit perhaps - there's a season for those again you see, I mean, you - naturally they wouldn't be shot during the -
 the - when they were having their young you see, but usually rabbits came into - into - the shops shall we say after the harvest you see. When the fields would be all clear, what I can remember of it now, and - there was rabbits then during the - autumn 
and winter I should think in abundance really those days. And rabbit was a - quite a - a good standby shall we say for any families then. Yes, and quite cheap you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Do you remember your mother having less food than the rest of you so you could all have a good tuck in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well I always felt somehow or other that my mother always denied herself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you ever notice whether she had less on her plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did she serve you and have no meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well - I couldn't say that I was - 
shall we say, really noticed it you know myself but as - as I grew older I noticed it you see when - you - you begin to notice things more perhaps when you gre}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654491\charrsid3146821 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821  a bit older and you'd notice things like that perhaps in the home you see. I think it was more 
noticeable shall we say during the war years, when we were very short of things then. And of course my brother working in the mine you see, I - I'm sure my mother denied herself - perhaps giving away everything for to keep him going you see and to - in th
e colliery. Otherwise I wouldn't say that - it was notic}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654491\charrsid3146821 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
able. I think my mother did deny herself a lot, with lots of things. But - it wasn't - noticeable from -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 She did it without showing you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. She would - I don't think that she
 would - show us because - she was a good mother and - they wouldn't do that sort of thing would they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Could you talk during the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes, we used to - used to - we used to have quite a chat you know during the meals. Although one thing I think
 my mother used to encourage us to talk. I don't know whether we talked much about - what we had given us or sometimes perhaps she'd only - we might have said that so and so was having more than you or something like that you see, but - that was on rare o
c
casions really. But we did used to - chat during our meals. Not too much mind, my mother'd - stop us if we were doing it too much but - she used to encourage us to speak then. Or perhaps it was - not for us too - eat our food too quickly might be. That wa
s might be the cause of it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh - usually you had to take what was cooked for you. There were no choice of meals really. It was - you know - 
if it was a - a broth or something like that well you had to have the bother whether you liked it or no you see. And - I know with certain and one meal that I used to detest and that was tripe. And that was a - a meal in those days of course you could hav
e
 almost from he butcher almost for nothing. But it - it - it was a good - it was a good - shall we say meal, they say that - I understand that there's a lot of - goodness shall we say in tripe. It was good apparently for you to take, but as far as the goo
dness was concerned, personally I hated it, I could hardly - almost - eat it. My mother used to make us eat it, yes. Whether it made us bad or no, it - she used to say it was good for you and we had to take it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What if you left some food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well usually if you left food uneaten there was something wrong with you. I feel - my mother used to feel you know that - there was something wrong with you because - food was not - I may say plentiful for us and - we had enough - I a
lways say that, we had enough, but - you didn't have a choice and - if it was a case that you left a meal it was a sign really that you were sickening for something or other and I think my mother used to treat it that way. Which was usually the case you s
ee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
If there was something on the table you wanted like the salt would you ask somebody to pass it to you or would you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well - those days I - if I remember, it was a very large cruet those days, the old st
yle cruet you know with - vinegar, salt, pepper and - whatever was the case, and that would be in the middle of the table. And - if - somebody was using a certain condiment well you had to wait until they finished and then - but usually we didn't used to 
u
se much of the - the - the - the cruet. My mother used to put all the necessary, shall we say - condiments and seasoning in the food that we - so we never used to use it very much. The only time that I can remember that we used to use salt was when we - p
erhaps we had an egg, you see, and you'd put the salt on the egg.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 And you could help yourself to it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 And you could help yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You didn't have to wait until she offered it to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh no. No. Help yourself, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Could you ask for a second }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654491\charrsid3146821 helping}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well - it was - it was rare really to have a second helping, if there was any there and you wanted it I suppose, but if it wasn't well you'd have to do with something else. If there wasn't enough shall we say of the meal, the mai
n meal that you had, and you wanted something more perhaps your mother would give you perhaps - perhaps a piece of bread and butter or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way or sit in a certain way at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Yes. Yes. Yes. Oh she did, yes, me mother - trained us you know the best she cold. She had plenty to do mind to see to everything but even so she - I - I can always remember her telling us now, sit up right and - used our - forks and - knife and forks as
 we should use them, and - this was very plain to me and - and - and I can remember it very well that when - they used to say to us, now, you are going to your aunt's or to your uncle for holidays, so you must be a good boy and girl there - and you must k
n
ow the way to use the - the various things you see. So that was really a way - in a way which made us do things you know - and that was one of the things that - mother used to always - hold on - on top of us you know that if we didn't do things properly w
ell perhaps we wouldn't be able to go for holidays again you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Were you allowed to bring a book to the table or a toy or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No. Never. Never. Whenever we went to the table the table was clear and it was for a meal only.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 When could you leave the table, as soon as you finished your meal or did you used to wait for everybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well usually on a weekend, when we were all down together I think we had to stop, and wait 'til everybody finished. But - in the weekdays we were not - havi
ng our meals together, and - it was a question you know that you didn't have much time perhaps for the - for the - especially the midday meal when you were away from school, you had to go and wash yourself and - and - run off as quick as you could to get 
to - to get back to school you see. So - there was no question of really waiting then for somebody else to finish. If you finished your meal - you would ask your mother and mother would say, say, yes, go and wash yourse}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13654491\charrsid3146821 lf and put yourself tid}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 y and off to school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 So would all the family sit at the table for a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Not - no, not - not - not during the weekdays, only on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What about supper or a meal in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well we never had a supper. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You had a midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
A midday meal and we used to have an - a - a tea and then there was no meal at all after that. And I thin - it was a good thing too in a way. Because - we would sleep well, and - you'd get up - in the morning and then you'd be ravenous so - whatever was p
ut in front of you - you - you ate it, and there - there was no question about - leaving it one side if we was in good health you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 It was only really on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Only on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What about Saturday, Saturday and Sunday you'd have meals together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well - those days you see Saturday was a work day even then you see. So there wasn't much difference with a Saturday. Other than them finishing earlier, a little bit earlier on a Saturday than you would on a - the other weekdays, because
 - about that time you know there wasn't a question of a - a five day week, it was a six day week and sometimes it was - it was quite full, you - you finished no earlier on a Saturday than you did on a - on a - on the other - day of - weekdays. It depend 
e
ntirely on what - job you were in. I know that when I was - when I was working - we used to finish perhaps early on a Saturday and - especially when we went to the goods department and - you - but mostly, you know, going back to the old - to that time and
 that date - Saturday wasn't much different from the others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 It was only Sunday really you were all together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Sunday was the only day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you have the same place at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Usually. Yes, usually. Usually mother was at the head and 
- and - the boys would be one side and the girls the other. I - I think we and the other girls we'd quarrel perhaps a little bit more you know, but - usual family little tiffs you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Who served the meal?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh by my mother. Yes. She might be assisted by my elder sister as she grew older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would she serve it out in this other scullery, put it on your plates or would it be served direct from a pot at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 It depends - depended on the meal. If it was the Sunday meal of course the jo
int would be brought onto the table and would be carved there you see. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Were the vegetables put in tureens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, they were not put in tureens. They were - they were served really, what I can remember - from the - the pots that they were cook
ed in. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Who would carve then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 My mother would carve, or perhaps my eldest brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would you remember how she served it then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes, yes. Yes. Well - I can't quite remember there, I don't think my mother made any difference reall
y amongst us at all, boys or girls. The one who was nearest and perhaps - you know, she might have done it in turns or things like that but - I can't remember anything shall we say that the boys were given any preference over the girls or one younger over
 the older ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Where did the younger brothers and sisters sit before they could feed themselves, you were the baby of the family weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 I was the baby. Yes, I was they baby. No, that wouldn't apply.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Yes, I think she was. She - she was - see in a very high service before she was married, and I think the - the - that played a big part you know I think in her life. I think she mode}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654491\charrsid3146821 l}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 led herself if possible on the people who she'd been livin
g with you see. And - and tried to bring us children up the same way I think because - the homes that she was in had children there and probably she noticed this, and noticed that you see, and - played a big part I think in how she conducted the home you 
see in every way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You mentioned earlier that she was with a rather well known family in Swansea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 She was, yes, they were big ship}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654491\charrsid3146821  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 owners in Swansea at the time. Name of Glasbrook. And - it was a very big establishment, their home was - they had quite a lot of servants there and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did she show you affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh yes. Yes. Yes, my mother showed quite a lot of affection to us all. I can always remember - we used to go to church with her you see and - to chapel and - I was quite, as I say t
he - the baby and I used to sit next to my mother and she used to have these big muffs those days you know they used to put the hand in, I used to put my hand in like that you know when she was - we were sitting down, 'course I didn't used to take much no
t
ice of the sermon but - probably I'd go to sleep you know at the side of her. But - I think my mother - after my father's death you know - she had us children and - well, you know, she lived for us then shall we say you know. Put everything that she could
 to - she realized you see that it was depending - everything depended upon her so much. And - I can remember you know - feeling that way, and I always felt that way right up to her death you know that my mother thought so much of us and - and was -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 If you'd had any worried then would you have been able to go to her and share them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh indeed yes. In fact we could always go to her. Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 How do you think she expected you to behave towards her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well - well - I don't know - I c
an answer that in a way how she expected it but I think we used to show - quite a - love and affection for her you see. Because - whatever she wanted, and I can remember her being ill on occasions you know, and she would - she would be in - bed probably a
nd - I as the baby of the family can remember many times taking up a cup of tea to her you know and - in bed, and she would think the world of that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did she bring you up to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654491\charrsid3146821 behav}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 e towards your brothers and sisters in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes, we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654491\charrsid3146821 - she wouldn't allow - any - nas}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
ty quarrels or anything like that in the home. She would allow you to argue away you know and - do things - and I think she used to enjoy it really, it brought you out you see and you - you - she didn't sort of - put a 
- a damper down upon you at all in - in - that sort of way. But - it - she would never allow us to quarrel nastily or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would she tell you to hit back if another child hurt you, would she encourage you to stand up for yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well - well - not that I was a bully in any way or any shape or form that way but I - I - I felt that I could always - defend myself when I was in school. I can remember my brother, my elder - the next brother to me you know - having - various tiffs with 
other boys and of course they would have it out you see. And - I think I carried on the same way to a certain extent you know and - I was quite capable shall we say then of looking after myself in any -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What would your mother say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh I went hom
e many times with a black eye - and a bleeding nose too. And - after perhaps a scolding from her she would - that would be the end of it you see, she wouldn't bother any more, she knew very well that - that it was a - two of one and three of another you s
ee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What sort of a person do you think your mother wanted you to grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well - my mother used to speak about her own brothers. My uncles who were - who were - farmers you see. And especially one that was her eldest brother, and he was - h
e turned out eventually to be a - a local preacher with the - with the - the Methodists, the Wesleyan Methodists you know. And she used to - always - when it came to be a question of - of referring to anybody who we should follow and grow up and act like 
it was always my Uncle Emanuel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 And she had no husband then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, that's right. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 It was nice she had her brothers to refer to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. That's - yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Do you think she stressed the character of your career, was she keen for you to get on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well - yes. Fortunately I was the only one of the family that had, shall we say, a higher education. I happened to pass - high enough in the elementary school to go into the county school at Porth you see and - I think my mot
her then knowing that was the case, and also that - I had - not been shall we say a robust child by any means and probably with the feeling that she thought, well, I'm not going to leave my children, all of them, at least all the boys, go into the mines -
 
I was fortunate probably that - in that way and I went to school you see. And - I don't know really what would have happened really if I'd stopped at the Porth county school but - the war was on you see, the '14-'18 war and - it would - it was coming to t
he question that everybody really, we all had to - help in some way to keep the home going and then I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What did your mother think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh she wouldn't allow such things under any circumstances. No. I doubt that we didn't use different wo
rds you know outside - because - I think - those days - we used to feel that we were growing up if there was a - a swear word you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 When the grown ups were talking were \{ILLEGIBLE\}.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Sometimes. But usually if the elder - especially the older
 - people were in the house, it was a question of, you know, little children must be seen and not heard. But - sometimes we would, you know, to, you know, to sometimes - use a little expression or say something or other but - not often because you weren't
 really - quite - up to the standard shall we say of what they were speaking about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What about if there was political talk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well - well - I can't remember any - political talk being used in our home at all. We were not politically shall we say - minded then.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 If you did something that your mother disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well - I'd be admonished by my mother for sure, and if it was of a very serious nature I got a few - canings from her. And it was up to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Always your mother was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. All my mother, yes. My father you see wasn't - he was - he was dead you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 But no one else would punish you, it was always your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh no. Oh no, my mother. My mother, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What did she do with you now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 W
ell - she would box your ears for you probably you know and - or - whatever the case may be, but - as I say it depended entirely upon the - this - the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Do you remember any particular occasion when you were punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, I can't - I can't rememb
er. I did have a few - you know, when I - thought that felt that I had gone over the mark entirely, and - she - there was one particular instance I can remember, but I didn't have a - a caning for this by any means. It was a question of - a friend of mine
 
who was a much smaller boy than myself - and - I - I must have done something to him you know when we were playing or something, he must have come up to my mother and told her what I'd done to him or something and of course my mother thought that this was
 
very bad on my - in my case because I was - so much bigger than - although I wasn't older than him, he was older than me and - I always remember that but - she made me - apologise to this - boy for what I'd done you see. What I'd done I - I - I did, I don
'
t know, I can't remember by any means but - it was - I must have perhaps - pushed him down or held him down or rubbed his face perhaps in the - in the - ground, or - you know, as boys do you see. But - that's about the only time really that I can remember
 - having my mother admonish me for doing something to somebody else. Another boy.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 But when she made you apologise she didn't punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You said you remembered how you were caned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 From your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What would that be for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well I can't remember. No, I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Was it on your hands?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh no, on - on my behind. Yes. And off to bed. Yes. Well it wasn't - it wasn't a very heavy caning, it was just a - one cane was enough be
cause - that was enough to - to make you feel that you were - you was - very - been a very bad boy and - it wasn't a question of a - a schoolmaster or schoolteacher admonishing you. You - you - the fact that your mother gave it to you, that was enough. It
 made you cry profusely. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 How did you feel when she made you apologise to that boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well after it I wouldn't apologise. I felt that I - I was - you know, and I didn't feel that he should ever have come up to my mother to tell her such things 
you see. But she made me and I had to apologise to him in the end, and I remember telling him, and I'll never speak to you again. But of course, in another hour we were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would you say that you received the ideas you had about how to behave from your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh yes. Oh yes. It was entirely - it was entirely in the home and from my mother that we had any - the upbringing and all the questions of right and wrong was given to us by her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No one else really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, we might have perhaps had - 
something - of our schooling mind was to a certain extent of that way as well because - teachers those days you know would - wouldn't allow things to - to be done shall we say - wrong, if you did things wrong well you were - you were caned for it, you wer
e
 - you were - and - I would think that the home and the school and to a - quite an extent as well the church that we went to, that was as well. Because you were taught - you were taught there you know the religion and - and you knew the right and wrong fr
om that you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh indeed, yes. Oh that was the big day really of - of your life, other than shall we say Christmas Day. Those were, shall we say, the two days which - which were
 outstanding as far as your young - or my young life was concerned was your birthday, and - Christmas Day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would you receive any presents on your birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, I - I wouldn't say that we did. No. The only thing that I can remember, the differenc
e was on a birthday was that you had a birthday party. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You had something special to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You had something to special to eat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 A tea party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you have friends, guests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 We - there was - yes. We - we might have - b
ut it wasn't on a large scale, you might have been allowed perhaps to invite one. But it was mostly, what I can remember, a family affair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Everybody would be there to tea that day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. Yes. And we'd have quite a lot of family between us all you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 That was on your birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 On your birthday, yes. Sometimes -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What about Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well Christmas Day of course, well - maybe I - it's almost - it was outstanding, no doubt it Christmas Day because we did have presents then
. And - not of any large ideas like - shall we say - motor - cars and all various things like that that boy - children get today, and aeroplanes and toy aeroplanes and toy this and that, but - it was - you might have a small present but I think - what I c
an remember, that if we did have a present - something really which was worth - or substantial - it might have been clothes or something like that you see. Which was useful to you and of course which was something that you required - as well you see.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Do you remember doing anything specially with your mother on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
No, I don't - can't remember doing anything special. It was a question really of children, you know, enjoying themselves, and - and enjoy ourselves we did as best we could you see. Not as we had very much but we - it was a very happy time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You played games and had a special meal did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes, we - we - yes. I think mother used to enjoy - in - would join in perhaps you know - in the afternoon perhaps you see. The gam
es that we used to have those days was - such as - a new draught board. And draughts you see. Or perhaps a ludo board. Those are the games that I can remember really that we had when we were young. There was nothing else actually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would your mother play with you or would it just be the boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Mostly the boys and girls you see would play. But - sometimes - my mother would have a game with us, especially a game of draughts you see. And - we got - quite proficient in draughts. You know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you have any musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 We had a piano, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Who played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
My sister was taught - pianoforte lessons. And - she - she did very well too in it. And then of course - when she - she was playing the piano and - my b
rother, my eldest brother who had a very nice baritone voice, he had voice training and of course - we used to have - sing-songs then in the house you see. It was very handy that we did have the piano - the piano and my sister was able to play, and then -
 we would - enjoy ourselves around the piano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You would make music together on the piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 On a holiday time or Sunday evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Mostly on a Sunday evening, yes, mostly on a Sunday evening. Where you'd sing - hymns and things l
ike that and - perhaps somebody - a visitor might come and - they would sing a solo you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Were there any books in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. We - we - there wasn't much - reading shall we say, I don't think we ever had a - a daily paper those da
ys. We - I don't think we even had a Sunday paper. But I can remember. But - whatever books there were were books which were given to us by the - church or - from the library that - which was in the chapel and - there was no magazines or things like that 
b
ought, as I say - we weren't in a position really to - buy them. And I don't think that - every home - did have those sort of things, I - it was only the higher - class shall we say were able to afford such things like that, used to have a daily paper. Go
ing back to those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Do you ever remember your mother reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 She didn't have much time for it. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You can't remember seeing her sitting down reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, no, I can't, no, not much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would she ever read aloud to you or your older brothers and sisters read aloud to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Or read to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
I think - I can remember my father, he must have purchased these books of the Boer War you see, the Boer War finished about 1902 was it or something like that, and -
 we had four volumes of the Boer War. I forget the names of them now but I know was one With the Fight to Pretoria. And - After Pretoria, the gorilla warfare which took place you know. And - of course I remember Kitchener and Lord Roberts you know they we
re the main men then of the British Army and - I used to read those books profusely and watch - look at the photographs you know and see the - I remember all the battles you know, the battle of Spine Cop and - and the Rel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13654491\charrsid3146821 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 ef of Ladysmith and etc. etc. etc. 
And - I was very very interested in those books, actually whenever I wanted to read and had time it was those books I would catch hold of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Were they the only books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 I would think that those were the only books that we had then. Yes.
 Yes. Except the Bible, we had the Bible, we had a few Bibles. We had the old family Bible you know, the big family Bible, all - various entries was - marriages and births and deaths and everything was put into the book you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You don't remember ever reading aloud to one of the other brothers or sisters or them reading to you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, I can't remember that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Do you ever remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. I remember my step-father. I had a step-father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 When would that be, that would be after 1918 would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, this was - this was about 19 - yes, about 1919 I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You don't remember a funeral any earlier than that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Not a funeral. No. I can't - no. No. My - I - my sister and my - sister who was buried - I don'
t remember her. I was too young, yes. No, not otherwise, there wasn't no -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You don't remember attending a funeral at all up to 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No. No, I can't remember anything of that description whatsoever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Were you ever taken out visiting neighbours or friends or relations, you went on holiday didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 But did you go out just visiting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well - yes, we were - we were brought up you see - there was families around us you know and - we were brought up, they had - children of al
most the same ages as ourselves you see. And then - if there was a boy of my age, well I'd be friendly with him, I'd go to his home you see, or he would come to our home you see, and we would play around the streets with all the various - young boys and o
l
der boys - of those days you see. And that - that was really our - where we made our - our fun you see. It was - it had - all made yourself, you - you - there was no question of - of things being arranged for you and done for you those days, if you - made
 your own - enjoyment, well it was that way you see. Other than shall we say - things that were held in the church. Otherwise it was - it was - you - you had to do it yourself, and and make your own sport and fun you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 There were no relations actually living in Treorchy near you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh in Treherbert. No. The - the nearest relations were down at the Mubbles, Swansea on my father's side, and - and then - in Somerset on my mother's side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you ever go out shopping?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Very rare.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Were you taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Very rarely, only time if I was taken shopping probably would be if my mother took me to - buy something, a pair of shoes, but usually you have to remember those were bought you know from the shops, say shoes, and you t
ried them on at the house you see. And - if they didn't fit well of course you'd have to have a - send them back and get another pair. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You wouldn't go with her to the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No. And as I think I mentioned before my mother made practically all our clothes until we got quite a good age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Do you remember any outings with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well - as I say we used to go down to - Somerset for our holidays mostly or to - the Mumbles, to an aunt of mine down there in Swansea. - There was one 
- time when we - if we went to our uncles in Somerset they farmed out on the Mendip Hills. Now there was no railway to take you out there whatsoever. There was a railway you know going down to Frome and places like that but there - but it wasn't near to t
h
e Mendip Hills. Now - if we went there for holidays we would have to go on one of these - carriers as they called them, from Bristol. You'd go to an inn in Bristol, and this would be a horse and cart and he'd be - delivering all the way, right out to the 
M
ednip Hills to various shops, you know, parcels and this and that and he'd carry you out as well as passengers. Now, I remember once - going with my mother and the children, my other brother and sisters, we were going to our uncle's, which one I don't kno
w
, but we got to Bristol in the night. Now, those were cheap fares those days on the railways, you travelled by night you see. And we got to Bristol and we couldn't get any further. And my mother was in the waiting room there and we children - over the - I
 
- I can see the - the - the Bristol temporary bridge now, as it is now - although they've taken down the bridge which was inside the large, you know, canopy which was there over the - the rail - the - the station, and we were running about there in the mo
r
ning, early in the morning you know, up and down these stairs keeping ourselves warm. But - that one outstanding thing I can remember, going on our holidays with my mother. Otherwise the only outings that we used to have was with the - the Sunday school. 
A
nd they used to go in those days then to Aberannan mostly. Barry wasn't thought of those days, we'd go by - to Aberannon by the old Mumbles Swansea Bay railway, through the Pennine Trail and down through the Avon Valley into Port Albert and to Swansea and
 - Aberannon beach you see where we'd have a real fine day there on the sands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 When you went away on holiday how long would you go for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh, we would go - we would go perhaps for a - a few weeks. I don't know the circumstances really because my br
other was working you see that - at that time and I would think that - I can remember going down there you know, we'd go down together perhaps and have a fortnight's holiday and my brother and my mother would return home you see. And she'd leave us there 
then as children because we were from school you see, and we'd stop there the whole month of course and then we would come back at the end of the month. She would come and fetch us probably.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you go regularly each school holiday or just the summer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh the summer mostly, yes. Summer Bank Holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You would all go then the mother and the older boy come back and leave the younger ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 That was always to Somerset?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well - not always, sometimes we would go down to the Mumbles I daresay you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 To your father's people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 To my father's, yes. To my father's -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you stay as long there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. Yes, we used to stay down there and we - and we - we got so used to the boys and girls who were living in the sam
e street there that we used to - you know - they used to look forward to us coming down there. And we would have a splendid down there really, come back from there, you know looking fit and well really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Only the school summer holiday you would go away, not any other time of the year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, not any other time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 On the Somerset holiday you'd be helping on the farm would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes, that's right. It'd be usually doing - the harvesting you see. And - I can well remember now the cutting of the c
orn you see and coming to the last - part you know, we started round the field and then all the village would be out there as well you know, waiting for the - like us - all of a sudden you see the - the cutter would go through the main and you would see t
he rabbits running up there in their hundreds. And hares and I don't know what not. And - then we'd be running after them you know and - oh dear, it was great was that really. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 When you were at Mumbles you'd be playing with the people in the street?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Yes, and of course we'd go down to the seaside there you see, every day we'd go down to the - to the - to the Landon Bay, little Landon Bay and Landon Bay which was not very far from us, and - we'd stop there perhaps, we may take our - our - lunch
 down with us you see. Boys and girls and - we'd be - we'd be bathing in our - in our - bathing suits practically all day long you see, have a meal then and then return home in the late afternoon - tired out you know, and - off to bed and - sleep all nigh
t then. Yes. Oh they were really fine times really, you know. You - you really enjoyed yourself. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 How did you spend Saturdays at home in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 I don't - well - we never went - we never went anywhere, there was - it was only really in la
ter - latter - there was an opera house in Treherbert I remember, and they used to have these various variety shows there you see. And - they used to have these eistedfo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654491\charrsid3146821 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 ds as well but I was a bit too young for that those days. But - the cinema didn't come
 to - Treherbert, not until - after the first world war as I can remember. Or just - no, just before the starting of the war, first world war. And - the only time that we would go there probably would be to a matinee on a Sunday - Saturday afternoon you s
ee. Where it - probably we'd have admission for a penny I would think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What did you do on a Saturday, Saturday morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh Saturday morning I - when I was quite a boy I had various jobs to do in the house. I had to do various chores you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 And you were doing the lather boy job weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh that was - that was - yes. That was a little bit, shall we say, further on you see. But - I did - have this job as a lather boy in the local - one of the local hairdressers there and shaving saloons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 When you finished that the Saturdays then you were in the Higher Elementary school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
That's right. Yes. Yes. That's right. Yes, that's right, I had plenty of home work - work to do and - and mother thought that - you know - to do that and do it well - well, it was no good to have been anything otherwise you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would you go to football or anything like that on Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh played football, yes. Yes. We - we - we used to make our football, our own, a rag football. Tie rags togeth
er you know. And - and - sometimes we would go down to the local slaughterhouse and wait for them to kill a pig, and then they would throw the - the pig's bladder to us. We made a football out of that. You know, and we would play with that you see, we - w
e were - never had a ball, a proper football to - that we bought to play with. Oh no, that was - that was out of the question. Whatever - things we had we had to really make ourselves you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would you play Soccer or Rugby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well anything, a kick around you know. Yes. Yes. We would play Rugby sometimes
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 A fine Saturday you'd be out playing really would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Almost, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 In the summer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 And in the summer as well - you know - depends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 On a Saturday what did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 We
ll - the mountains you see were very handy to go up to - to climb as well, we used to walk over the mountains quite a lot. Roaming round the hills, which were very very pretty and very nice, the air - the air up there was a - was clear and as sweet as cou
l
d be you know, it was - it was - and it did us a lot of good, and we used to climb these mountains and then walk for miles and miles you know. And we'd take perhaps a meal with us again, perhaps on a nice June day and - off we'd go you know. Gang of boys 
together and - we wou}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654491\charrsid3146821 ld really - just go where our no}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 ses take us sort of thing you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What about Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh Sunday we had to attend church. Morning, afternoon and night. We went to church in the morning and we - and then we went to Sunday schoo
l in the afternoon and then in the evening usually we went - I went with my mother. She wouldn't go in the morning because she'll be - cooking the meals and one thing and another. But - as I say the afternoon was Sunday school and then in the evening - yo
u went to church with your mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would you have different clothes on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh yes, you had your Sunday best clothes. You had a - a suit which was always kept for - you know - as best, and wore it only on a Sunday and for special occasions shall we s
ay. And that's about the only two - two suits you had. One - one suit for - the weekday and the other one for Sundays you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What about playing games on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh no. No, you were - my mother tried to keep us, you know, to the - the straight 
path you know as far as - that sort of thing was concerned. Yes, Sunday was a holyday and it was kept - may be kept - to be kept holy.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 So you didn't play any games, they thought it was wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 They thought it was wrong, yes. I'm not going to say
 that we didn't if we were away from, you know, from the jurisdiction of your parents. We sometimes transgress you know, but - usually, you - you - if you went to - to - to church in the morning you see, you'd have your - your best clothes on, you wouldn'
t
 go and play football games then you see. By the time you came out from the service on Sunday morning well it was time to go home and have your midday meal. Well then after that - you usually went to Sunday school. Well - sometimes after Sunday school if 
you had a bit of time and I think I remember I used to - we used to go up the mountain then for a walk you know. Walk with the boys from your same class in school. Sunday school. And then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Your mother thought it was really wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh indeed, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 And your mother attended a place of worship with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What denomination was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Congregational. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 How often would your parents go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh my - my mother}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654491\charrsid3146821  - we - we would go - on a weekend }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
nights as children to the - the Band of Hope as they called it. Where we had - slides shown us you know. And of course we used to sing all the songs you know, the - that were - suitable for - the teetotalers you know. And - and then my mother of cours
e would go to some of the week night services, prayer meetings and things like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 And you children would go three times on Sunday and she'd go twice would she on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, once. Once. Unless it was a special occasion, if there was b
ig meetings in the church she'd probably make an effort to go you know, in the morning as well, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 There'd be two week night services probably would there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes, I'm sure there was one - no, there was the week night service I think - which
 might have been on a Wednesday and then there was the prayer meeting as well which was usually Thursday probably you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 But you wouldn't go to those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 It would only be the Band of Hope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 There were Sunday school outings you said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Was it always Aberannon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Usually. Yes. Yes. That's right, it was the nearest place, and it was the better place too I think for - for schools you know. It was such a wide open expanse of sand there that it - it - it was first class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 One day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 One day. All day, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You would go on the train then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Go along the Swansea railway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 It would take you practically down to the beach?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes, almost you know, we'd have - the - it was running along the side of the - of the - of the dunes in Swan - Aberannon, - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 A special train?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Yes, a special train, that's right, for the Sunday school because there would be the parents and - a lot of people come as well who were not actually - attached to the Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Were there any other social activities organised by the chapel that you took part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, not anything at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Nothing like Rac}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654491\charrsid3146821 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 obites?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well I think that'll come under the - the Band of Hope you see. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Was there a choir?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes, we had a choir there, yes. But I was a bit too young then. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You weren't in the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No. No, my brother - my brother was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You said he had a good voice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 So you weren't in the choir at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What did the choir do, did they have their trips and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
No, I don't think so, they - they - they - they would - they would - lead the - the congregation you know in singing and - probably - they would do, shall we say
, a cantata or something like that during the Easter maybe or - something for the Christmas as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did the chapel have a temperance club, the Band of Hope was wasn't it really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 But it wouldn't have a Rac}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654491\charrsid3146821 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 obites club sort of thing attached to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 I don't think so, there was a Ra}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654491\charrsid3146821 cc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 obites evening and I think you know in Treherbert what I can remember but - how it functioned I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. My mother usually. But if there was a visitor - they always used to ask them to say it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would it be every meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh no. No, it was usually - usually at the main meal on the Sunday when we were; all there. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 If a visitor came they would say it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Asked, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Yes. Every night we used to say our prayers. My mother used to teach us you know to - when we were quite young you know, then of course we'd say - say the same prayer practically every night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you ever have family prayers all together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 On a rare occasion. Very rare occasion. I can't remember. No. No, no I can't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You said them just before you went to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 That's right, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You said your family were interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
No. I - I think my mother had enough to do to - to look after us and bring us up as best she could you know, politics didn't - come into it very much. Well it - you know - those days politics were not - considered - the thing shall we saw for the workin
g class you know. You had to be an outstanding man or woman to - be prepared to voice your opinion those days, not that it - it did change in time for the better we know but - well the fact was that you - it was - it was almost you know in those days that
 
you weren't allowed even to - to be in a trade union you see. It was only just, shall we say, going over the - the - time shall we say of the - the Merthyr riots and - and all those sort of things you know. And - trade unions ever weren't - weren't recogn
i
sed you see. I know that the Miners Federation was - the strongest shall we say in being I think those days but even - in - in that case you see you were - you were - you were looked down upon if you belonged to it, if they knew that you belonged to it an
d if you were prepared to - to speak your mind, well you was a - almost an outcast sort of thing in the society.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You mean employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes. Employers. And not only the employers and - the people who - who - thought that they were, shall we say, 
of the - the middle classes, those days you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You don't remember your mother voting in a general election at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, but I think that if she did vote, which I - I think she did you know when the occasion arose, our local M.P. was Hyweth Mand
on then you see - and - I'm sure that she would have voted for the Labour party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Because some people did think they were risking their job or their house, because the house was sometimes tied to the job wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh they were. Oh yes. Yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you brother have the vote, your oldest brother would have been old \{ILLEGIBLE\}
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well what I could remember those - well, you see, those days - for you to have a vote, what I can remember, you had to be a householder. It isn't the s
ame as today. You see? I - I - I'm - I'm almost certain when I say this now that - that if you didn't have a house of your own well you didn't have a vote, a Parliamentary vote. You may have had a local vote, you know, for the local council, but I don't t
h
ink that you were allowed a Parliamentary vote unless you was a householder. Well of course fortunately or unfortunately see my mother - we were a householder you see. But there was - thousands in the valleys who - who - living there who never had - the h
ouses weren't theirs, they were renting them and then they didn't have a Parliamentary vote you see. That did change eventually I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 But you felt that there was pressure there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh there was pressure of every kind I think. Yes. You see Mabber 
himself was a Liberal, he wasn't a Labour man properly, a Lib-Lab he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 The Liberals were strong then weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 So there was no one in your household a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No. I mean I don't think my - my - my
 - my brother, my eldest brother who would have - he wouldn't have had a vote you see. And I don't think he would - I don't think he would have had a vote in any case until he was twenty-one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 So your mother was the only one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 She wasn't a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 She never worked for any parties at the elections?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh no. No, no, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh we had to walk. Yes. It wasn't so very from - from our home, shall we say about a - quarter of a mile.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 How long would it take you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh - well - I don't remember going as a very small child but - when I went to the boys school which was almost in the same vicinity it would take us - we used to always - mostly run to school yo
u know as boys you see. Or kick tins along the - the old - lanes as we used to call them you see and - depended really. But - if you went to school direct from the home it'd take you perhaps say - five minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Who went with you to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh wh
en I went to the - when I went - I can remember going to the - the boys school we went on our own. Perhaps my eldest brother might have taken me first of all you see because he was in a higher class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 And you had your midday meal at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 I used to enjoy it really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You liked it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh we respected them very much. Some more than the others. Especially when it came to the question of punis
hment because punishment was allowed then by the school - by the teacher you see. They had canes there you know and - you - behave obstroperously and they would - they would punish you you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did they emphasise certain things as important in life, like manners, tidiness and punctuality and the way you spoke?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Not so very much. The - the - the important thing those days was the three R's you know. Reading, writing and - arithmetic you see, those were the main things. Until you went into a higher school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 If you did something they disapproved of they punished you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 With a cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 On the hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 On your hand, oh - and sometimes on your backside. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Were the girls caned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 I don't know. No, I don't know what the girls - what the girls -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What sort of thing would you have to do to have the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well perhaps talking too much in the class and not taking notice of the teacher you see, things like that you see. I don't think I can remember doin
g anything shall we say real - naughty out of the way. I know that - specially in the summer months - you know, we'd be playing perhaps and not come into school as we should or there to time. I often used to find the schoolmaster at top of the steps there
 and as each boy going back there'd be a crack across your back as you went through you know. But - I often think today, well, yes, did me a lot of good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did your mother show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes, I - I - I think my mother did with
 me especially I - I don't know - a little bit more time I think and - I don't think I ever quite shall we say so - strong a boy as - my other two brothers were you see, I - I was born with a hernia you see and they considered it you know and looked at it
 
in every way you see and I wasn't - it wasn't put right by operation - 'til I was eleven years of age. Well then of course they had to be very careful with me to a certain extent, and I think my mother always thought, well, we must - do something about th
is young land and - not let him go to work underground which - thanks very much, I - I never did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did she ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes, I think so, I - I can't remember very much about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did she ever go to the school, visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, I don't think so, they - there was never any call actually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Or meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did the other children in the school come from similar types of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh indeed, yes. Yes. Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 All assorted children in the school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh they were all types and - you know, from various families. There was no question of - of any - any question of - there were no boarding schools or anything like that in the Rhondda Valley you see. The only - di
fference really shall we say in the valley would have been - by - say - not - profession, I mean by - either you were a - a Non-conformist or you were - or you - Church of England or you might have been a roman Catholic you see. And I think there was a - 
there was a Roman Catholic church the only one was in Tanypanddy. That's the only difference I would think. That children went to that school. Because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 I think th
at they would concentrate on the brighter boys. You see? If - if they found that you were - were - shall we say - not able to grasp things - well - you see they - they had to show results to a certain extent, it was coming those days when teachers had to 
show results you see. And I feel sometimes that if you were - were - a tr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654491\charrsid3146821 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
er, you know, that they would give all the help to you you see. In preference to other boys who - didn't show any aptitude at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh yes, gangs. Oh we all had gangs, yes. There were gangs of boys - and - in the different - age groups you know as well. Gangs in your school, in your class you see. And - not that it was really gang warfare but you were - you were - you were gangs, 
you see, you sort of - from the same district perhaps you see. You sort of kept together and - wasn't so obvious as all that. Yes, the street gang yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Were there any children who weren't in gangs and were left out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh there were some, yes. Ther
e were some of the - who - I forget the name we used to call them but we - they were some boys and girls you know were from homes where I think the parents, especially the mother would say, oh you - you mustn't go and play out with - with so and so or so 
and so and that sort of thing you see. And they - when they went home they were kept in the home and that sort of thing you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What about the other school you went to, Porth County School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Porth County, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would it be the same then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh it was a high - of a higher - higher description altogether there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 How old were you when you went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 I think I was about - eleven or twelve I think. Something like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You had to try the scholarship did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Tried the examination, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 How did you feel about it in the junior school, was everybody put in for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 I think you all could try. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did everybody try?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well I wouldn't be certain like, I can't see that you did, everybody had to you see. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you have to do special work for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
I - no, there wasn't a special - specialisation as there is today, it was just a question of - how - how you were shall we say in comparison to the rest of the class you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 When you went to Porth it was a boys school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Boys school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 How long did it take you to get there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh went by train then. By train from Treherbert to Porth, and then walk from Porth station to the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 How long would it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well the train jou
rney would take about a half an hour I - if I can remember. And then - you walked up to the school which was up on - outside the - boundaries actually of Porth, it was between Porth and - and Tanypandy and it take us - easily ten minutes or more to walk t
here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 So you had three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654491\charrsid3146821  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 quarters of an hour really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 And you had to get to the station in Treherbert?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Weren't very far from the station there, five minutes shall we say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you go on your own then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes. On my - on my own, there was other boys of course from the same - from Treherbert. Yes. All went together, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would you have your midday meal at school then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 At school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you have to take sandwiches?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 We had sandwiches and - the only thing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654491\charrsid3146821  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
that we had otherwise was - there was the tuck shop in the school there, and during - I forget what we used to call it now - recess, that's right, in the morning recess we would go down to the tuck shop and I can always remember buying a - a - a dough boy
 you know. One of these dough boys with jam through the centre of it. And used to give a ha'penny for it. And that was - and we considered that to be quite a delicacy you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What about midday dinner, would that do for your dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh no, we -
 we took food with us for our midday meal. Sandwiches, there wasn't much else. Might take - might take a banana with you, something like that and - bread and butter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Meat sandwiches?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, I don't think it was meat. It was usually bread and butter
 or - some fruit and then you would have a meal then when you came home you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What did you think of Porth County School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh when I went to Porth I - I - I - I - I really enjoyed it there. It was - you know, something - something altogether di
fferent you know to what we - had in - Treherbert in the Elementary school. You - you know - I think - I - I did at least, I felt you know that I was going into something - a new life altogether. You were - different teaching and the teachers were differe
n
t as well. You had to learn Latin you see. And French. And - all the various subjects which we never had in - in the elementary school. Algebra and geometry you know and things like that you see and - it - it was a new - new life altogether. I did quite w
ell too in school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What did you think of the teachers there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well - it was the beginning of the first world war you see when I went there. 1914 I think it was I started there, that's right, I must have been eleven you see. And - some of the teach
ers who were in - the military class were called up and had to go, and then the - they put - women teachers in their place. Mostly. I always remember that the French master, he was one who had to go to the war and then they put a - a French mistress in hi
s place.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What happened there if you did something they disapproved of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh there was no caning by the - by the school - not by your form masters. But you - you had a form master but he didn't take you in all the subjects you see. He was probably, shall we say a - a mathem}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13654491\charrsid3146821 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 tician and if that's the case he would take the; whole of the school right up to the - top forms you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 But they didn't cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did anybody do any caning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You were sent into the schoolmaster's - to the schoolmaster himself, the he}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13654491\charrsid3146821 admaster. Yes. But that was a r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 are occu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654491\charrsid3146821 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 rence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 How would he punish then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well usually there it was lines you know, you had to write out so many lines. I must not be such a naughty boy or - five hundred lines something like that, and that taught you to - to watch what you were doing - you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would that be the punishment the headmaster would give as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well, it was very rare for him to cane you. I was never caned there. Not once. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did your mother take an interest in your work there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh I think yes when I started there, I was the only one of the family that ever went to a higher education.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did she ever go to the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Nor met the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did the children there come from similar homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh yes, from - from round the area you know, the both Valleys, the Rhondda Vall and the Rhondda Vach and - the area which was, shall we say, covered by the Rhondda Urban District Council you see, which would be th
e - from Porth up to Mardi in the Rhondda Vach and in the Rhondda Vall right up to Treherbert and Blaumondau you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 But the children in school - with you wouldn't all be from working class homes would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well - not all, some would be perha
ps sons of - shall we say - teachers and - colliery managers and - whatever you might like to say, you know }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654491\charrsid3146821 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821  trades}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654491\charrsid3146821  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 men}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654491\charrsid3146821 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 s sons and daughters you see. Doctors, yes. Doctors.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 So all children really went to that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. There was no difference at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment in the Country school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
No, I don't think so. There was a system there you see that if you didn't - try yourself well - that was up to you. And you fell down otherwise yo
u see. If you were good - if you showed good results in your - in your - examinations at the end of the terms you went, shall we say, into a higher form in the next year. For instance, when I went into Porth I was - I think I must have been fortunate real
l
y to pass the elementary examination because I only just scraped in I think. And I was put into a form C. There was a form A, form B and form C. Well I was in form C. Well, I did so well in the form C I think I was either the first or second in the - form
,
 and - then in the next year, there were two forms made. A form A and a form B, there were so many boys who were left school you see. For various circumstances, I don't know what. And - but I immediately went into form A, so I - I must have done very well
 you see. And so on you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Were there any gangs there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 I wouldn't say so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you go round in groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well - no. I don't think that - it was not - it was - it was not - encouraged at all, that sort of thing. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You didn't feel there were any children there who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No I don't think so. No. I think they - now their characters had been developed a lot more you see when you went there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 How old were you when you left Rorth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well I - I - I think I was about - what - I was about fourteen I think. Fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would you have stayed on longer if you had had the chance?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh indeed. It was 1917 when I left and - I had to leave to help to keep the home going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you attend any evening classes after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh I did subsequently you know. I went in for shorthand and things like that you know and I - when I joined the railway it was advantageous to - be able to do shorthand especially those days. And I attended - evening classes in sho
rthand. And I had private tuition as well with it you see. But that's about the only thing I did. I did a little bit of home - the - woodwork - evening class as well. Where you could make things you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh no. The only thing I regret is that I didn't go further, that's all. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 And you think you benefited from going to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh indeed, yes. It showed you really the advantages you know - of a higher education And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 When you were working as a lather boy you said there were two brothers who employed you? Oh
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What did you feel about the work, did you like the work you were doing there or did you dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh I - I don't think I liked it by any mea
ns. No. No, it was something that was - shall we say - yes, something really that I knew I was helping the home - I - I disliked it more I think because - men was coming in there you know, they'd been drinking and you could smell their breath and all that
 sort of thing. And it - it was a menial kind of a job you see. Lathering somebody else's face you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did this job alter your attitude to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 The job you mean? I don't think so, no. I wasn't there very long.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You didn't have any other part time jobs did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Then you left school at fourteen to go to the railway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Railway. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What exactly were you doing then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh I was a junior clerk in the booking office in Treherbert.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 How long for, were you there until the end of 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Just the one job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Yes, well - yes, I think so, yes, until the end of 1918, yes, that's right, in the booking office, and parcels office you know which was combined.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What have you done then since the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh on the railway, yes. Yes, I've been on the railway all my life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 But you left Treherbert did you, you didn't stay in the booking office?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, I went from Treherbert - I went - in Treherbert I went into the traffic office as the
y call it there which is a part control then, you know, control of the - of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654491\charrsid3146821 the railways - under the old t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
rail you see and - and then I went from there into the goods office. And from there I went to Treorchy, I was transferred to Treorchy the next station down, in the goods department. And then I went to various stations after that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Until you retired?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Until I retired, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would you have preferred another sort of job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well - looking back you know, it - it's been very interesti
ng, the railways were very interesting and - the only thing that I regret is that I didn't - shall we say specialize a little bit more, I might have gone on much further than what I - I did, although I - I - I finished up as the chief clerk in Pontypridd 
which was quite a - a - something you know that - yes, yes, yes. Oh yes. In fact Pontypridd you see was the only goods station to the whole of the valley then. And they had about -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You were on the goods then were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 I was in the goods department. Once I left Treherbert I - I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 So you were chief clerk of the area really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you have to have a training period or anything, no apprenticeship of course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No - on the railway you see of course you could attend nigh
t classes there, school classes. I went to Cardiff to the - Technical College you see, in Cardiff, I went in for - railway law, railway economics and - all the things which - connected with railways which was very interesting of course really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 The railway arranged those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 In the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 In the evening, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 That wasn't straight away when you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh no. It was when I - after I'd been to - to - to Treorchy, when I went to Treorchy I started going then down 
there. Of course when I - when I entered the - the examination you know in Treherbert - I had to go over and see the stationmaster and he gave me a - a - a slight examination in his office there you see, reading and writing - and a few sums you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 On the job you were trained in Treherbert?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 When you went to Treorchy you'd had a leg up really, then you went to Cardiff?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. That's right. Yes. Yes. That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you belong to any trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. I belonged 
to the Railway Clerks Association, which was the only - trade union then covering shall we say the - white collared - workers you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you take part in any of it's activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Eventually, yes, I used to attend the branch meetings and - I ev
entually got to be the Chairman of the branch, I attended - eventually as a branch Chairman the - the - the yearly conferences you know, I went to Dublin and - remember going there once and - as a representatives you see of the branch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 So you took an active part in the union didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well, yes, yes, slightly active part, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you feel that the employers and workers and the same interests in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh no. Well - you - you didn't have really much feeling about it, all you kn
ew was that you were employed and you - you had to do your work and you got paid for it you see. It was up to you to do your best in the job you were doing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you feel that there were divisions of interest amongst the workers, some people say in tho
se days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers, you mentioned that living in Treherbert there was definitely a feeling what the craftsmen in the pits were better than the workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well - yes. Oh well, if ever - if you got a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Was it like that on the railway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well yes, we considered ourselves you see in the clerical jobs, we - we were salaried staff you see, and if you were salaried staff you considered yourself - you were considered in fact - the employers, y
our employers expected you to consider yourself shall we say, you was a - an officer of the company you see. And as an officer of course you - you had to give orders, and you had to see that those were carried out you see. So - that was the difference ent
irely. Although there was engine drivers and all other class - of men you see as far as the - working - or they were - they were considered as workmen where you was an officer you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh - no, not very much, I don't think so. The older you got you see, you - you - you naturally changed your - attitudes and one thing and another, you got your - more responsible and - and that job got more responsible shall we say -
 so did you you see. At least you should anyway, I did I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You only did the one job, it was very stable employment really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. Yes. Never lost a day in the whole of my life we can say. I - I lost through illness mind but I was never - didn'
t lose ever - ever a day's pay. Because we were paid you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you continue to live at home when you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes, until I - let me see - about -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Up to 1918 anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes, up to 1918.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Or with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well - I can't think it was very obvious to me, all I knew was that I - I had a job of work now and it was a responsible job and of course - I took my money
 home and - and I was very glad to give it to my mother to help to - and - which was making thing easier shall we say in the home you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You wouldn't notice any difference with your brothers and sisters because they were older than you and they were already working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
The only difference that I felt really was once was when my eldest brother who by this time was a proper miner you know, he had a stall of his own in the colliery, and - he was - wanted my mother to let me go and work with him in - 
in the mine, but my mother wouldn't have anything to do with it at all. That's the only thing I can think of. Otherwise -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you spend Sunday any differently after you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, I still attended the - the local church you know. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes, and Sunday school, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you take an interest in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well, yes, I just mentioned I was the - the chairman of our branch you see, we - was naturally connected with the Labour - party see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 It was because you were a trade unionist really that you were Labour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
But the - the strange part is this do you see, although you were - were shall we say connected with the Labour movement - as a - a - the Railway Clerks Association even we - considere
d ourselves shall we say a higher - even in the Labour movement you see. When I go back -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You didn't consider yourself one of the workers really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well - no, that's right. There were workers you see and the - and - and the artisan class as you might say you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Why did you think that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well it - it made you - it made you feel that way because - the company themselves made you feel that way. You see, for instance now when I started work on the old Taff railway there was a - an - a - the
re was a rule, you had a rule book given you you see, and one of the rules in that was that you had to present yourself - at the - at the office of the railway company in a clean and tidy manner. You had to wear a - a - a black tie with a - stiff collar a
n
d a bowler hat. Yes. And that was only broken down - by the war intervening and I know when I went there it was - I don't know - I can't remember actually having a bowler hat, I know I did have them subsequently, but I don't think that I was capable of pr
esenting myself - on those lines because of the war you see. They were not available. So - so that - that in itself made - made you feel - the job made you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Although you were affiliated to the Labour movement?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes, exactly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 There were different classes in that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Yes. There was that - there was that feeling you know that - if it came to a strike well - we were not considered as strikers you see. And it was - it was - it was quite out of the - out of - thought in any means that you should
 ever go out and strike you know. I know we came out on strike in 1926 but that's going outside our - our boundary now. But - you see, it take a - it took a lot of breaking down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 It took the general strike to get you out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You wouldn't have gone out on strike otherwise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh no. No. No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You wouldn't have voted in an election before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No. Not old enough, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You didn't take part in any political activity other than at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Only the union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 That's all. That's - that's - that's the only thing. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 After you went to work how did you spend your spare time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well - 'course I was quite young then you see. Quite young. Yes, fourteen you see. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You don't remember what you did in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, not really. Played with the boys you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You still played with the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You didn't make any new friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No. No, not really, no. It was much later really that you developed, you know, into various other angles of -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You didn't have any special boyfriends or girlfriends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You didn't take any home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you have to get home by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes, even then I think, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 After you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Yes. Oh yes, you didn't have any licence by any means, it used to be those days you know, you had to wait 'til you were twenty-one you know to have the key of the door sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 And your mother wanted to know where you went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh yes. She still kept, you know - tabs on you you might say and - saw that you, didn't - well, I - I think you know, I was quite young you see. Still quite a boy you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 And she expected you to be home by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes, I think we had to go to bed about nine o'clock I think, even then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 If your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh - well, unless it was very serious you know and it was very rare that she had a serious illness - we would
 look after my mother you know and - but - mostly, if it was required - somebody to - you know, who knew exactly what to do, one of the neighbours or friends would probably come in you see and see to - various things you see and than my sisters or - my br
others or myself would - help my mother you know, and - until she recovered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, not anybody. Not relatives - anywhere near - actually within shall we say - thirty - twenty-five, thirty miles, I wouldn't think so.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did your parents have any friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes. Quite a number of friends in our - street where we were. And friends - who we knew - in the church, the chapel you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Those were your mother's friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Were they ever invited into the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh indeed yes, they would come - they came around to see you you know and - probably it would be - you know, to enquire after - if your mother had been ill or something like that and missed you perhaps in - the ser
vice you see in the chapel, they would come and - see you you see. And naturally they'd be asked in and - they would go - either to the bedroom where your mother was or if she was convalescing well - they'd see her then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 But they wouldn't come at times other than when your mother had been ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh sometimes they would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would they call casually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. - Casual. Not regularly, I don't think so, not regularly, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would they have anything to eat or drink with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes, a 
cup of tea maybe, something like that you know. But - it wasn't a regular thing those days you know. Meals were kept to a certain time - what I can recollect. It's not like it is today you know when people come in well - cup of tea straight away shall we 
say you know, that sort of thing. And - there wasn't much of that sort of thing, not to my recollection anyway.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Were friends invited to the house on any particular day or occasion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 I think it did develop, there was a - there was one particular f
riend of my mother's - she was the wife of - of - the local brewer in Treherbert and he had - he was - the brother of Sir Percy Hill, of Hereford Cathedral, and - they came to live in Treherbert and when they came there - first of all they came and they -
 
my mother gave them lodgings. Now perhaps - and they stayed with us for quite a while I should think and then eventually they had a house of their own and then of course - the friendship then was maintained you see. And - to be shall we say know of a - a 
Particular friend I think that Mrs Howell was one particular friend, who would call you know, or we would go there, my mother would specially go there you see. -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would she call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes. Yes. Yes, there was no need for invitations at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would you say once a week or just now and again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 I don't think it was any regular - no, it was a - casual, you know - if you came along and, well - there you are you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Neighbours wouldn't come in and out of the house much would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Yes, sometimes neighbours - there was a neighbour in - in our street, a Mrs Roberts, and their family, and they had quite a number of children and as I told you before we played with - our contemporaries you see in their family
, and - Mrs Roberts especially was a good friend of my mother's and - right to a - quite a ripe old age, where they - continually kept - you know - visiting one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 So your mother went out to visit friends and neighbours just as they came in to see her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Yes. Not - not very regular because as I say there was quite enough to do at home you see. This did develop - a little bit when - when we children grew a bit older you see and she had a little bit more time to herself you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 People often say that in those olden days they made their own amusements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh indeed, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What do you think your mother would do when she went to visit her friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh I think they'd have a chat about things, nothing else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 They wouldn't be making music or anything like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh no. Not in my mother's case. Yes. She did - she loved music mind and - and but - I don't think she was developed so much as all that to be able to - it - was at about the general things you know of life you see. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Many people divide society into different social classes or groups, in the time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one social class and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes. I think about that time you know there were the working c
lass as we call them shall we say, and there would be middle class and of course there was the - the top notchers really. And - I think we were just about on the border line really of the working class, there's no doubt about it, we were. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Who belonged to the same class as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well all the - all the men who were working shall we say in the colliery, on the railways or any particular jobs, other than shall we say the professions you see. When you get up to the professions - of course if my fa
ther had lived most probably we would have been - accounted in that class. I would think so because as an over}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654491\charrsid3146821 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
man in the colliery he was considered to be of the higher, you know, there was the vicar and the schoolmasters and - the ministers and etc. etc., who shall we say were considered to be in the middle class there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You mentioned the upper class, who would they be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well the only upper class I would think in our town - shall we say would be the colliery manager. He would be something -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 He was definitely a cut above the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 I would think so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Above the vicar and the schoolmaster?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 I would think so, yes. Yes. Because he was the - you know - he - you wanted a job well he was the man who would give it to you. And if he
 wanted - if he wanted - he gave you the sack well you would have the sack off him and of course - there was no -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 He didn't own the colliery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 He wasn't the owner. Oh no. But - he was considered in the - the - vicinity those days you know as one 
of the high top rankers as we'd say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Can you ever remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well - I always - I - I always gave respect where it was due myself and we were taught to do it as well 
by my mother. But I never considered anybody shall we say personally myself - better than I was, if you understand me. I - I - I would - although shall we say we - we - we were - we were not affluent by any means - I still had that feeling in myself that 
I was as good as they were. And - but I - I never shall we say - used that in any way because I respected everybody, I - and I - and - whoever they were I would give the respect that was due to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Were you taught to lift your cap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes. Yes. Oh indeed, yes, the boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 To whom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well to any ladies that you met you see. Oh yes. Yes. And - and especially as I grew a little bit older it was the thing those days of course to raise your hat whenever you passed them on the street, and espec
ially if you passed them - or you came in - came in contact with them to have a conversation, you rose your hat and - and passed the time of the day and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would it be only to ladies or to any men, any older men?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, not to men, no. Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Was there anyone that you called sir? Or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well - no, not in my younger days, when I started work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 That'd be about 1917 would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. Yes. The stationmaster then I would - I would - I would call him sir, yes. Whenever he came -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 The minister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
No, not the minister I wouldn't, no, no. But - in work especially, that was the first time I think that I - you know - gentleman concerned was a Mr Venn, I know I started at the railway station and - he was a very fine 
man and - and - I think we were taught to respect our elders and especially in the question of employment, you - you give him the - necessary sir which - I don't think it was made any servile - manner at all, just a question of respect that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your mother in that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Oh yes, if we were with my mother I think we'd go along the road you know, usually - I don't know if I ever went with my mother anywhere unless I went to the doctor's or something like t
hat you know, and - other than to - chapel. And if you passed people that you knew they would - doff their hats and - either walk along with you or - or - if you passed one another - that would be the case you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 So in Treherbert the most important person was the quarry master you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes, in our town, yes. Well we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Who were the most important people of all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 The colliery managers, there was a few collieries there you see, five or six collieries and they were all managers you 
see, and they all lived in rather - bigger houses, much bigger houses which were - supplied by the collieries and - I would think that - there wasn't any - any such - shall we say - there was no manufacturing - or - or shall we say factories at all in our
 area, it was just the mines - and the railway. And then the few professions you see. So - he would be - the managers of the collieries were considered to be the top notchers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you come into contact with them at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. There was - one of th
e managers was a - he was a manager of one of the biggest pits in Treherbert, the Fernhill collieries - a Mr Jones, and he was - also a deacon of a church. And - I can remember him well you know sitting in the big seat as we called it you see in the - in 
t
he - English churches, the setval of course in the Welsh and - and - why I remember it so much is that his daughter, who was much older than me of course, she taught me in Sunday school, she was my Sunday school teacher. And - in fact she's living now in 
the present time in Cardiff here, she married one of the Segars you know, ship builders. Ship owners in Cardiff. And he was a very fine man you know, well built man and well respected too in the town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 So you'd only come into contact with them in the church, not outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Through the church. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Who did the shopkeepers in Treherbert associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well all the shopkeepers of course were - were - there was the grocers and the - and the drapers and - all the various - shall we say - sh
ops, bakers etcetera you know, and - you found - they - they were family businesses mostly, there was none of the companies then as you find today, and - usually - the families either went to - one type of church or another you know - shall we say the Bap
t
ist church or the - Congregational church and there was the Welsh as well as the English you see. There was the Welsh Baptist, there was the English Baptist and so and so with the Congregational you see. And - there was the Church of England and there was
 the Welsh Church of England as well at those days, before this disestablishment you see. Well -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 So they really associated in the church or chapels you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 I think -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Not really outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No. I - and I sometimes almost think you know
 - that - they went there no doubt they - they were - that way minded but even so I often thought sometimes, well - there - there was a mixture in various churches for trade you see. And - when I look back upon it in that respect you see I think I - yes, 
there was a grocer in one church and you know and a grocer in another church and that sort of thing. And a builder in one church another thing, and they had - you see, they had - various trade through being associated that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Who would the clergy be friendly with or mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well of course the - the - the - the ministers of the churches naturally would look after their flocks you see. And - they would come around periodically visiting you if you weren't going to church so often, I suppose they'
d come around and want to know why you - why you weren't not there, or if they heard you were ill naturally they would come and see you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would they be friendly with the colliery managers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 I think they were, yes. I think would because most of the
 colliery managers you see went to the churches as well, the various churches. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Were there any farmers around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh there were a few. A few farmers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 They wouldn't come into Treherbert really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well - they were actually - just outsid
e shall we say on the hills you see. I don't suppose they had much time really to come to church as far as that's concerned because those days farming was much different to what it is today. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh, teachers in the schools, yes. And -
 and - and - without exception I think most of them went to church. They were attached to churches. And - you see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Chapel or church?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. There was a connection in every way you see with the schools and the churches.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 And there were no employers really in the Treherbert?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Only collieries - and the - and the shopkeepers you see, they would employ -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What sort of people would you say went to the church, the Church of England and the Church of England in Wales?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. Well mostly 
the people I think - if I can remember, that went to the church were - shall we say - people who came into the - the towns from shall we say England I think mostly. You could tell them you know, they were really English people. There were a few mind becau
se there were the We}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8673088\charrsid3146821 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 sh church as well you see, but it was sparsely attended. What I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 So the native inha}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13654491\charrsid3146821 b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 itants of Treherbert would tend to go to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes, chapel. Non-conformist Welsh, yes, oh through and through, yes. Yes. Oh
 the churches were full, absolutely full those days you know. Yes, you could - you - unless you went to church shall we say ten minutes or a quarter of an hour before the time of the service well - you - you didn't have a seat, unless of course you had a 
pew of your own. Sometimes the churches - you had a special of your own you see. And you paid for it I think, I don't think that we ever did but - that was the case those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same stand
ard of living or would you say there were different standards in the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well - well even in the working class you see there was some - men shall we say who had regular jobs you see - shall we say - winders in a colliery now you see they w
ere considered a - shall we say a little bit higher than - you know, the - the - actual miners you see, and then there was the - then check}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8673088\charrsid3146821 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 weighers again you see, they were considered - shall we say slightly higher, and not only that you see - if ever the
re was - they were out of work on a strike well those men were on the staff and they - they would be employed. They never lost any time you see. And if you were a salaried man shall we say those days you was considered a cut shall we say above the - the o
rdinary - working man you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Do you think they felt superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh I think they did. I think they did, yes. Oh yes. And I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You were conscious of this as a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh I think so, yes, and you - and - and you treated them that way too.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 According to the father's job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh very rough some, yes. Very rough. I - I often - I often saw you know outside the various pubs there, public hous
es, men being - fighting in the - in the pubs and coming out and fighting on the roads and that you know. It - it - it - when I - when I consider these films that we see today sometimes you know of the old - American Rush to the Klondike and I don't know 
w
hat, not - I always think of the Rhondda Valley, and saw what I used to see as a little boy there. And - but strange to say you know it was a very strange thing you know on a Sunday morning everything was quiet. There was not a sound or anything. You see,
 
there was not motor cars those days, there was very few horse - mostly - mostly horse, and on a Sunday it would be only the milk that would be delivered, you could say that was all, but you saw the change, like as if - like as if - peace was reigning ever
ywhere. And - even the families that we considered to be rough, even so they would keep confined to their homes you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Would they go to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 There were certain families who lived near you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes, around you know. It was - it was a mixture, a proper cosmopolitan - even in the - the - the class of people and the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You meant mainly drinking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Drinking, yes, and fighting and - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Was there cock fighting in Treherbert?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Cock fighting, yes. Yes, there was. I never saw it but there was. Yes. There was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You would consider them to be rough, the people who attended that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. And of course they kept pigeons and - pigeon races you know and money being - banked - or backed this way and that way yo
u know and - and then of course there was boxing tournaments and all that sort of thing that used to come to the place there. I remember the old - boxing manager by the name of Scarrot you see, he had a boxing booth and - Jimmy Wilde was - he was brought 
u
p in his previous - his - early boxing days you know with these - in Scarrots boxing booth and that used to come to Treherbert sometimes you know just to - to all the towns in South Wales. And then there'd be boxing then on a Saturday night you see. The m
e
n coming from the pubs would be asked to take on perhaps one of the boxers of Scarrots you see. And if you could last - one or two rounds he perhaps had ten shillings for it. Then shillings mind you. And even those fighters, well - I - I - I've heard it s
aid about Jimmy Wilde himself that - he - many times fought, you know, for - a pound or two you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you ever go to watch the boxing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, not when I was a young boy. No. I did go eventually, some - when - boxing was coming out of, shall we s
ay, the old fisticuffs style you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Some families were considered rough and there were others who were consid}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8673088\charrsid3146821 e}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 red respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh indeed, yes. And - and most of the people that went to church were of the respectable ones you see, the ones who 
didn't they were considered the rough ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You feel there was a distinction between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes. Yes. Craftsmen were shall we say - although they were the working class, they were shall we say the elite then of the working c
lass you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did your mother have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well I think she - she knew the people were that were in better circumstances shall we say you see. And - if that - what you mean, I - I - I - I think she did - appreciate that position.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did she see herself as belonging to a particular social group do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
No, not those days. Because as I say my mother hadn't got much time for - shall we say to mix with any higher - the higher or the lower you see. She was well employed in the home. And kept to the home you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did she mix with other people like shopkeepers, in the chapel I suppose, the chapel was a mixed community wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 That was the only place where you would mix.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 She mixed with all the groups there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 The working class, middle class and the upper class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. That's right, you - it was a - shall we say a - a higher and lower working class you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Was there a difference in the chapel, was a colliery manager in the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh - I think - oh yes, oh there as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 The deacons would try and run the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh they would. Yes, oh well - oh yes, they would - they would - if they were in that position you see - and it came to shall 
we say a very important - business you see, well I think that those people even there in the church were considered that they had the last word you know. Oh I think so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Even within the chapel community?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. Yes. It permeated the whole community. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You still felt there were different strata?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Do you remember anybody going from one class to the other in Treherbert while you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well - no, I couldn't say that I can remember anything like that, I mea
n - things were very - were slowly - you know, developing those days you know. There was no question of winning a - shall we say a football pools or anything like that. If you were - if you were - say poor it took you a long time shall we say to get out o
f that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
You don't remember anybody while you were there by virtue of education or marriage going from one - a working class person marrying a middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes, well of course - as I say, although - although I've mentioned that there were those 
classes, it wasn't so very obvious shall we say. You see? It wasn't so very obvious because - we were all living in the one - town or village and although you had the manager living perhaps just in the same town and he had a bigger house and all that sort
 of business there wasn't - so much difference, no. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 It wasn't clear cut really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Not - not as you find - not as you find it today.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. There were - I th
ink the manager's wife that I - I spoke to you about previously Mr Jones, the manager of Fernhill, his wife was a very nice lady. She was - and - and she - she - you know - she conducted herself that way as well. They - they - there were - there were - th
ere were some very very nice and ladylike people around those days you know. You don't find it today so much I don't think. They - they're whole attitude you know, in ever way, was ladylike, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What about the men, would you call anybody there a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
The men - there - there were - yes, there were a few I think, there was one particular man, he was a deacon in our church - Mr Evans they used to call - his name was - and he was a tailor by the way, and - nicknamed then, of course, yo
u see as Mr Evans - there were so many Evans' and Jones' and one thing and another that they - that's the reason why they were nicknamed. And he was named Mr Evans the cutter. Now he was a perfect gentleman. He was very tall - although he had a - shall we
 
say a Welsh name, I think, Evans is a Welsh name, yet he was a Scotsman. And he was a tall man, six foot so much, and I remember him coming to church you know with a - frock tail - top hat. You know. Awful lot of people wore them those days you know, come
 to church on Sunday - morning coat you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 And you remember him as being a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. I used to always think that he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Why did you think that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well - well he - he - he was always so nice to people. He wasn't - different
 to one or to the other you see. And - I think that makes a gentleman you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Do you ever remember seeing a policeman around where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes. There was always policemen around - in the town there, and they showed themselves those days, 
of course they had no motor cars or other means of transport and - they'd walk the streets you see. And - and - if we - in any way got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8673088\charrsid3146821 obstreperous}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821  in the parts where we were playing - you would find the policeman coming along and once he showed himself - we soon made ourselves scarce.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 What did you think of him, did your mother ever say if you were naughty, I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes. Yes. Yes. Sometimes. Yes, well there was one - there was one policeman there we used to call Bobby Brimson, I rem
ember him very well. He was a fine big fellow you know - the policemen today not near the size they were those days, and - of course there was - I think there were a lot of - Irish men - you know I - came into the police forces, especially in Glamorgan th
ose days. They were considered the finest police force in the country. For their - stature you see. I don't think that any man was under - ten foot - five foot }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8673088\charrsid3146821 ten and a half in their stocking
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 ed feet. And - the - mostly on the six foot mark you know. But I 
remember this policeman very well you know and he lived - not very far from us and - strange to say my mother - was rather friendly with his wife too. And - but - you know, I look back on it as a bit of fun in a way because - you know - the policemen were
 there to see that - that you didn't sort of overstep the mark you see, there wasn't much crime really in those days. Not - not -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Why do you remember this man, because he was friendly or looked after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No, no, not - not in any way. Not in that - we were - we were rather a bit afraid of him I think. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 How do you think policemen treated the people in Treherbert on the whole.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well if it was necessary for any rough stuff they were able to give it. There was no doubt about that. They 
were - they were big enough, and I often - I often saw men being - taken you know down to the police station - perhaps on a - not usually in a weeknight but on a Saturday especially when they had the - you know, they'd be - drinking perhaps heavily you kn
ow and - fights would occur and if a policeman come there - you see - if they wouldn't - disperse peacefully well then - that's all he had to do was to take them down to the police}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8673088\charrsid3146821  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 station, I often saw men being run down by a policeman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh no. It was our own property, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Do you remember having a feeling that your mother had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Oh yes, after my father's death especially. Yes, we were quite young you see all the family were quite young an
d - we - my mother - had to - work very hard I think to keep - things - you know - make ends meet as far as we were concerned. I know we did have help from her brothers, my uncles in Somerset, but even so - it was a - a struggle you know from morning 'til
 night. Lodgers and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did you think about it when you were little, were you conscious of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
No, I wasn't so very conscious of it then, no. I - when I look back upon it of course I can see what my mother went through, but - but - those days - it 
wasn't made obvious to us, I - I had a very very - when I - although - you know, we didn't have much money I think I can honestly say that I had a very happy childhood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You didn't realize really that you were so hard up?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No. No. No. And I think
 - and I think my mother never let it - appear that way too. She was content and - and - and - and it was a pleasure to her I think to be able to do things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did she ever have to get help from the Guardians?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 No. Never. No, no. She would never go 
to them. Because it was considered those days if you went to the - to the Parish as they used to call it those days you know - they would call it - oh, he or she is on the Parish, and you were considered one of the lowest of the low you see to do that. Bu
t - I - my mother never did. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 She'd only have help from her brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 If there was somebody in the area who the people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Well some -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 In some areas they made rough music or effigies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
No, I wouldn't think it was so bad as that although there were - I think eventually you know that sort of thing - it - it - I think the lowest shall we say or the roughest or the - people - went to live in differ
ent quarters of the town. I find - you find it everywhere today somehow or other you see. In the slums or whatever the case may be, and there was a part of Treherbert which we considered - you know - where shall we say the - the roughest or the lowest of 
the low went to live. They were very cheap rented houses you see and of course probably that's why they went there. And - that's bow things I think developed there, as I think developed everywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Did the people show that they disapproved of those people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 
Well that's the only way that they - they only way they showed it was that they'd say, well - you'd better keep away from that quarter, you see. Not that there was I don't think any of real harm there actually. But it was considered rough quarte
r and the - the least you had to do there or go there the better for you you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 You were never given lessons by your mother or a tutor, you went to school didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10571796 CL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1902656 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 Do you remember how old you were when you first went to school?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs20\insrsid10512340\charrsid3146821 

\par }}